(68, 'Anatomy', 'PM2400. Muscles of mastication', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\793\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Muscles</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Origin</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Insertion</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Action</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lateral pterygoid</td>\n<td>\n<p>Upper head - Infratemporal surface, sphenoid bone</p>\n<p>Lower head - Lateral pterygoid plate</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Upper head - Pterygoid fovea&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Lower head - TMJ capsule and articular disc</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Depresses mandible (with suprahyoid muscles)</p>\n<p>Jaw protrusion</p>\n<p>Grinding(Side to side) movements</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Medial pterygoid</td>\n<td>\n<p>Superficial head - Maxilla</p>\n<p>Deep head - Lateral pterygoid plate, Palatine bone</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Angle of mandible</p>\n<p>Ramus of mandible behind mandibular foramen</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Elevates mandible&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Jaw protrusion</p>\n<p>Grinding(side to side) movements</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Temporalis</td>\n<td>\n<p>Temporal fossa</p>\n<p>Temporal fascia</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Ramus of mandible</p>\n<p>Coronoid process</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Elevates mandible</p>\n<p>Side-to-side movements</p>\n<p>Jaw retraction</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Masseter</td>\n<td>Zygomatic arch</td>\n<td>Ramus of mandible</td>\n<td>\n<p>Elevates mandible</p>\n<p>Jaw protrusion</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/8682ae3ead154d7c8c9ac439a714e155x1279x1400.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/a663026380df4d5dbe4f265e393e9407x1280x1287.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/c28a6ebb37304b3e8aeaa285e8840a23x1280x1288.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(69, 'Anatomy', 'PM2397. Modifications of Deep cervical fascia', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p>The deep fascia in the neck is condensed to form the following layers:</p>\n<p><strong>I</strong><strong>nvesting layer -</strong>&nbsp;It forms the roof of the posterior triangle and splits to enclose:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Parotid gland</li>\n<li>Submandibular gland</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Pretracheal fascia -&nbsp;</strong>It splits to enclose the&nbsp;thyroid gland to form its false capsule. This capsule is thickened posteriorly and on either side forms the suspensory ligament which is known as the ligament of Berry.</p>\n<p><strong>Carotid sheath</strong> -&nbsp;is formed anteriorly by pre tracheal fascia and posteriorly by the prevertebral fascia. It encloses:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Common carotid artery</li>\n<li>Internal carotid artery</li>\n<li>Internal jugular vein</li>\n<li>Vagus nerve&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Prevertebral fascia</strong> -&nbsp;It forms the floor of the posterior triangle and the axillary sheath. Inferiorly, it blends with the anterior longitudinal ligament.</p>\n<p><strong>Buccopharyngeal fascia -&nbsp;</strong>It covers the outer surface of the pharyngeal constrictors and the buccinator. Posteriorly, its separated from the prevertebral fascia by the retropharyngeal space.</p>\n<p><strong>Pharyngobasilar fascia -&nbsp;</strong>It fills the gap between superior constrictor and base of the skull.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/bd75f5b454334bb6854958c8ac664100x600x848.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(70, 'Anatomy', 'PM2268. Arteries supplying the cranial fossae', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Region</td>\n<td>Arteries</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anterior Cranial Fossa</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Anterior meningeal branches of anterior and posterior ethmoid arteries</li>\n<li>Meningeal branches of internal carotid arteries</li>\n<li>A branch of middle meningeal artery</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Middle Cranial Fossa</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Middle and accessory meningeal branches of the maxillary artery</li>\n<li>A branch of the ascending pharyngeal artery</li>\n<li>Branches of the internal carotid artery</li>\n<li>A recurrent branch of the lacrimal artery</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Posterior Cranial Fossa</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Meningeal branches of the occipital artery</li>\n<li>Posterior meningeal branches of the vertebral artery</li>\n<li>Dorsal meningeal and tentorial arteries arising from the meningohypophysial trunk</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Note:&nbsp;Meningeal branches of ICA do not supply the posterior cranial fossa.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(71, 'Anatomy', 'PM2242. Functional components of cranial nerves', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><div>\n<table border=\1\><colgroup><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Functional components of cranial nerves&nbsp;</strong></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Oculomotor: CN-3</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Extraocular skeletal muscles – GSE</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Preganglionic fibres to ciliary ganglion - GVE</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Trochlear: CN-4</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Extraocular skeletal muscle (SO)- GSE</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Trigeminal: CN-5</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Sensation from the face - GSA</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to 1st arch - Br E (SVE)</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Abducent: CN-6</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Extraocular skeletal muscle (lateral rectus)- GSE</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Facial: CN-7</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>General sensory from ear - GSA</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Special (taste) sensation - Br A</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to 2nd arch - Br E</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Parasympathetic to submandibular and pterygopalatine ganglia - GVE</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Vestibulocochlear: CN-8</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Hearing/balance - SSA</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Glossopharyngeal: CN-9</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Sensory from pharynx/tongue – GVA</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Taste - Br A</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>General sensation from ear – GSA</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Parasympathetic to otic ganglion - GVE</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to 3rd arch - Br E</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Vagus: CN-10</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Sensory from ear - GSA</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Sensory from pharynx/larynx – GVA</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Taste - Br A</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Parasympathetic ganglia in thorax/abdomen - GVE</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to 4th/6th arch - Br E</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Accessory: CN-11</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to 6th arch (through vagus) - Br E</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to sternocleidomastoid and trapezius - GSE</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><strong>Hypoglossal: CN-12</strong></div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<div>Motor to lingual muscles – GSE</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>abbr.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>A</strong> - afferent , <strong>E</strong> - efferent , <strong>Br</strong> - Branchial (word special (derived from branchial arches) can also be used instead of branchial, but due to confusion with special sensory (carrying special senses) its better avoided), <strong>V - </strong>Visceral, <strong>G</strong> - General, <strong>CN</strong> - cranial nerve,&nbsp; <strong>SO</strong> - superior oblique muscle.</p>\n</div></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(72, 'Anatomy,', 'PM2228. Superior orbital fissure', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/58e3dbd8d4244b95a597e4eb9198b732x600x865.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Structures passing through the Superior orbital fissure</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Above the common tendinous ring: LFT (Superolateral compartment)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>L</strong>acrimal nerve</li>\n<li><strong>F</strong>rontal nerve</li>\n<li><strong>T</strong>rochlear nerve</li>\n<li>Superior opthalmic vein</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Within the common tendinous ring: BAN (Intermediate compartment)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>B</strong>oth divisions of oculomotor nerve</li>\n<li><strong>A</strong>bducens nerve</li>\n<li><strong>N</strong>asociliary nerve</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Below the common tendinous ring (Inferomedial compartment)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Inferior ophthalmic vein&nbsp;</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(73, 'Anatomy', 'PM2139. Structures passing through skull foramina', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Opening</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Transmits</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Optic canal</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Optic nerves</li>\n<li>Ophthalmic arteries</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Superior orbital fissure</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Lacrimal nerve (V1)</li>\n<li>Frontal nerve (V1)</li>\n<li>Nasociliary nerve (V1)</li>\n<li>CNs III, IV, VI</li>\n<li>Superior ophthalmic vein</li>\n<li>Inferior ophthalmic vein</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Foramen rotundum</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Maxillary division of CN V (V2)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Foramen ovale</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>M</strong>andibular division of CN V (V3)</li>\n<li><strong>A</strong>ccessory meningeal artery</li>\n<li><strong>L</strong>esser petrosal nerve</li>\n<li><strong>E</strong>missary veins</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Foramen spinosum</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Middle meningeal artery</li>\n<li>Nervus spinosus</li>\n<li>Middle meningeal vein</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Foramen lacerum</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Deep petrosal nerve</li>\n<li>Meningeal branch of ascending pharyngeal artery&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Emissary vein</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Carotid canal</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Internal carotid artery</li>\n<li>Venous and sympathetic plexus around artery</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Jugular foramen</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Inferior petrosal sinus</li>\n<li>Meningeal branch of ascending pharyngeal artery&nbsp;</li>\n<li>CNs IX,X &amp; XI</li>\n<li>Sigmoid Sinus continuing as IJV&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Middle meningeal branch of occipital artery</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Hypoglossal canal</strong></td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Hypoglossal nerve (CN XII)</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Foramen magnum</strong></td>\n<td>\n<div class=\ng-scope\>\n<div class=\ng-scope\>\n<ul>\n<li class=\ng-binding\>Osseo-ligamentous (anterior) compartment:&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>Apical ligament and tip of dens</li>\n<li>Upper band of cruciate ligament</li>\n<li>Membrana tectoria</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Neuro-vascular (posterior)&nbsp;compartment:\n<ul>\n<li>Lower end of the medulla oblongata with meninges</li>\n<li>Fourth part of vertebral artery surrounded by sympathetic plexus of nerves</li>\n<li>Spinal roots of accessory nerves</li>\n<li>Anterior and posterior spinal arteries</li>\n<li>Tonsil of cerebellum.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\ng-scope\>&nbsp;</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/59dee8c948d642d8b7e732620bd2e2a7x600x1522.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(74, 'ENT,', 'PM1978. Muscles of larynx', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p><span>Remember 2 exceptions:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span>All muscles are<strong> adductors</strong>,<strong> except PCA </strong>(an abductor)</span></li>\n<li><span>All muscles are supplied by the<strong> recurrent laryngeal nerve</strong>,<strong> except cricothyroid </strong>(superior laryngeal nerve)</span></li>\n</ul>\n<table class=\t1\ cellspacing=\0\ cellpadding=\0\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Action</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Muscle</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Opening</strong> of the inlet of larynx</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Thyroepiglotticus</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Closing</strong> of the inlet of larynx</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Aryepiglotticus, Interarytenoids</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Abductor</strong> of vocal cords</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Posterior cricoarytenoid</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Adductor</strong> of vocal cords</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Lateral cricoarytenoid</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Tensor</strong> of vocal cords</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Cricothyroid</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Relaxer</strong> of vocal cord</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Thyroarytenoid</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span><strong>Modulator</strong> of larynx</span></div>\n</td>\n<td class=\td1\ valign=\top\>\n<div class=\p1\><span>Vocalis</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p class=\p1\><span><strong>Safety muscle</strong> of larynx: <strong>Posterior cricoarytenoid</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\p1\><span>Safety muscle of tongue: Genioglossus</span></p>\n<p class=\p1\><span>The muscle of <strong>whispering</strong>: <strong>Lateral cricoarytenoid</strong></span></p>\n<p class=\p1\><span><strong>Vocalis</strong> is known as the modulator of larynx because, the <strong>anterior part</strong> of the vocalis muscle can <strong>tense</strong> the vocal cord, and its <strong>posterior part</strong> can <strong>relax</strong> the vocal cord.</span></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(75, 'Anatomy,', 'PM1429. The sphenoid sinus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p>It occupies the <strong>body of the sphenoid</strong></p>\n<p>Ostium of the sphenoid sinus is situated high up in the anterior wall and <strong>opens into the sphenoethmoidal recess</strong>, medial to the superior or supreme turbinate</p>\n<p>It is lined by <strong>ciliated columnar epithelium</strong> with goblet cells. Cilia are more marked near the ostium, which facilitates mucus drainage into the nasal cavity</p>\n<p>Relations of the sphenoid sinus:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The<strong> lateral</strong> wall of the sphenoid is related to the <strong>optic nerve </strong>and<strong> carotid artery</strong></li>\n<li>The<strong> floor</strong> of the sinus is related to the <strong>Vidian nerve</strong></li>\n<li>The<strong> anterior</strong> part of the roof is related to the <strong>olfactory tract, optic chiasma,</strong> and<strong> frontal lobe</strong></li>\n<li>The<strong> posterior</strong> part is related to the <strong>pituitary gland in the sella turcica </strong>and&nbsp;the<strong> cavernous sinus.</strong></li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/face00ae45b44fa88a120a3723a3e6bex1280x1567.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(76, 'Anatomy,', 'PM1428. Nasal Septum', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p>Septum proper is an osseocartilaginous framework made up of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Septal or <strong>quadrilateral</strong> cartilage</li>\n<li><strong>Perpendicular plate</strong> of ethmoid</li>\n<li><strong>Vomer</strong></li>\n<li>Others – crest of nasal bones, nasal spine of frontal bone, rostrum of sphenoid, crest of palatine bones and the crest maxilla, and the anterior nasal spine of maxilla</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/057b97bf8e764f04b58aceffa9f4f3e9x1280x1399.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(77, 'Anatomy,', 'PM1424. Structures opening into meatuses of nose', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li><strong>Inferior</strong> meatus: <strong>Nasolacrimal duct</strong>, guarded by&nbsp;the valve of Hasner</li>\n<li><strong>Middle</strong> meatus: <strong>Frontal</strong> sinus, <strong>maxillary</strong> sinus, <strong>anterior</strong> <strong>ethmoidal</strong> sinus. All these together form the <strong>osteo-meatal complex</strong> or Picadle’s circle.</li>\n<li><strong>Superior</strong> meatus: <strong>Posterior ethmoidal</strong> sinus</li>\n<li><strong>Sphenoethmoidal</strong> recess: <strong>Sphenoid</strong> sinus</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/f5343a3b0bac4006b313352b92fd8c07x1280x1759.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(78, 'ENT,', 'PM1422. Boundaries of the nasal valve', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>Laterally:&nbsp;<strong>Lower border of upper lateral cartilage</strong> and fibrofatty tissue and <strong>anterior</strong> end of inferior turbinate</li>\n<li>Medially:&nbsp;<strong>Cartilaginous nasal septum </strong></li>\n<li>Caudally: Floor of the <strong>pyriform aperture</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>The nasal valve is the <strong>narrowest part </strong>and offers<strong> maximum resistance </strong>to airflow</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/4ddd3eb6e384496aaabb5e7b3eaaa1fbx1280x1022.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(79, 'ENT,', 'PM1405. Compartments of the parapharyngeal space', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><span><strong>Prestyloid</strong></span></td>\n<td><span><strong>Poststyloid</strong></span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span><strong>Relation to styloid</strong></span></td>\n<td><span>Anterior</span></td>\n<td><span>Posterior</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span><strong>Relations</strong></span></td>\n<td>\n<p><span>Medially: Tonsillar fossa</span></p>\n<p><span>Laterally: Medial pterygoid muscle</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><span>Medially: Posterior part of the lateral pharyngeal wall</span></p>\n<p><span>Laterally: Parotid gland</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span><strong>Contents</strong></span></td>\n<td><span>Medial pterygoid muscle</span></td>\n<td>\n<p><span>Carotid artery</span></p>\n<p><span>Jugular vein, IX<sup>th</sup>, X<sup>th</sup>, XI<sup>th</sup>, XII<sup>th</sup> cranial nerves</span></p>\n<p><span>Sympathetic trunk</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><span><strong>Presentation</strong></span></td>\n<td>\n<p><span><strong>Prolapse</strong> of tonsil&nbsp;and tonsillar fossa,</span></p>\n<p><span>Spasm of medial pterygoid muscle leading to <strong>trismus</strong></span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><span>The pharynx bulging behind the posterior pillar</span></p>\n<p><span>Injury to of CN IX, X, XI, and XII leading to&nbsp;</span><strong><span>vocal cord paralysis</span></strong></p>\n<p><span>Sympathetic chain injury leading to <strong>Horner’s syndrome</strong></span></p>\n<p><span>Swelling of the parotid region</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(80, 'ENT,', 'PM1294. Parts of Pharynx', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Part</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Cervical vertebrae</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Extent</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Structures</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Lining epithelium</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Nasopharynx</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Skull base-C1</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Skull base- palate</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Adenoids, ET opening, Torus&nbsp;tubaris, Fossa of Rossenmuller, Posterior pharyngeal wall (PPW)</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Pseudostratified ciliated columnar</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Oropharynx</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>C1-C3</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Palate-hyoid</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Base of tongue, Pillars, tonsils, PPW</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Stratified squamous</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div><span><strong>Hypopharynx</strong></span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>C3-C6</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Hyoid to cricoid</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Pyriform sinus, Post-cricoid region, PPW</span></div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div><span>Stratified squamous</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(81, 'Anatomy', 'PM1250. Divisions of Maxillary Artery and Its Branches', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/a2303ab13e0649d5b993147ad8be02c9x1280x1346.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>1st part/Mandibular part:</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Extend - Neck of the mandible to lower border of Lateral pterygoid</li>\n<li>Common Pattern - All branches from this part enter the bone.</li>\n<li>Branches\n<ul>\n<li>middle meningeal,</li>\n<li>accessory meningeal,</li>\n<li>inferior alveolar,</li>\n<li>deep auricular&nbsp;</li>\n<li>anterior tympanic arteries.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2nd part/Pterygoid part</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Location - In the infratemporal fossa</li>\n<li>Common Pattern - All are muscular branches.</li>\n<li>Branches\n<ul>\n<li>Artery to lateral pterygoid,</li>\n<li>medial pterygoid,</li>\n<li>Masseteric artery</li>\n<li>2 deep temporal arteries.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>3rd part/Pterygopalatine part</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Location - pterygopalatine fossa</li>\n<li>Branches\n<ul>\n<li>Artery of pterygoid canal,</li>\n<li>Infra-orbital artery,</li>\n<li>Greater palatine,</li>\n<li>Sphenopalatine artery,</li>\n<li>pharyngeal artery,</li>\n<li>posterior superior alveolar artery.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->');
