(753, 'Pathology', 'PM1993. Mechanisms of Immune Evasion by Tumors', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p>Tumors evade host immunity by the following mechanisms:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Selective outgrowth of tumor cells</strong> that do not express tumor antigens</li>\n<li><strong>Loss or reduced expression</strong> of <strong>MHC molecules</strong></li>\n<li>Upregulation of expression of factors like <strong>PD-L1 and PD-L2,</strong> which act on PD-1 receptors on T-cells and inhibit T-cell activation.</li>\n<li>Secretion of immunosuppressive factors like <strong>TGF</strong><strong>-β and</strong>&nbsp;<strong>galectin</strong></li>\n<li>Induction of<strong> immunosuppressive regulatory T cells</strong>, which could also contribute to immuno-evasion.</li>\n</ol></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/81b03c4a3cd44b26a44717cf2d7aa105x683x889.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(754, 'Pathology', 'PM1992. Tumor antigens recognized by CD8+ T cells', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Antitumor activity</strong> is mediated predominantly by cell-mediated mechanisms. <strong>Tumor</strong> <strong>antigens</strong> are presented on the cell surface by <strong>MHC class I molecules</strong> and are recognized by <strong>CD8+ CTLs</strong>.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Tumor antigen class</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Examples</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Products of mutated genes</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Oncogene products</strong>: mutated <em>RAS</em>, BCR/ABL fusion protein</p>\n<p><strong>Tumor suppressor gene</strong> <strong>products</strong>: mutated p53 protein</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Over/aberrantly expressed cellular proteins</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Overexpressed</strong>: tyrosinase, gp100, MART in melanomas</p>\n<p><strong>Aberrantly expressed</strong>: cancer-testis antigens (MAGE, BAGE)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tumor antigens produced by oncogenic viruses</td>\n<td>\n<p>Human papilloma virus&nbsp;proteins E6 and E7 in cervical carcinoma</p>\n<p>EBNA proteins in Epstein–Barr virus-induced -lymphoma</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Oncofetal antigens</td>\n<td>Carcinoembryonic antigen (CEA), α-fetoprotein (AFP).</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Altered cell surface glycolipids and glycoproteins</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>CA-125, CA-19-9</strong> expressed on ovarian carcinomas.</p>\n<p><strong>MUC-1</strong> expressed in both ovarian and breast carcinomas</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(755, 'Pathology', 'PM1986. WHO classification of Lymphoid Neoplasms', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\392\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>I. Precursor B-Cell Neoplasms</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>B-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma</p>\n<p>(B-ALL)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>II. Peripheral B-Cell Neoplasms</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Chronic lymphocytic leukemia/small lymphocytic lymphoma<br>B-cell prolymphocytic leukemia<br>Lymphoplasmacytic lymphoma<br>Splenic and nodal marginal zone lymphomas<br>Extranodal marginal zone lymphoma<br>Mantle cell lymphoma<br>Follicular lymphoma<br>Marginal zone lymphoma<br>Hairy cell leukemia<br>Plasmacytoma/plasma cell myeloma<br>Diffuse large B-cell lymphoma<br>Burkitt lymphoma</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>III. Precursor T-Cell Neoplasms</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>T-cell acute lymphoblastic leukemia/lymphoma</p>\n<p>(T-ALL)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>IV. Peripheral T-Cell and NK-Cell Neoplasms</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>T-cell prolymphocytic leukemia<br>Large granular lymphocytic leukemia<br>Mycosis fungoides/Sézary syndrome<br>Peripheral T-cell lymphoma, unspecified<br>Anaplastic large-cell lymphoma<br>Angioimmunoblastic T-cell lymphoma<br>Enteropathy-associated T-cell lymphoma<br>Panniculitis-like T-cell lymphoma<br>Hepatosplenic γδT-cell lymphoma<br>Adult T-cell leukemia/lymphoma<br>Extranodal NK/T-cell lymphoma<br>NK-cell leukemia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>V. Hodgkin Lymphoma</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nodular sclerosis<br>Mixed cellularity<br>Lymphocyte-rich<br>Lymphocyte depletion<br>Lymphocyte predominance</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(756, 'Pathology', 'PM1970. Various actions of Principal Mediators of Inflammation', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Histamine</td>\n<td>Vasodilation, increased vascular permeability, endothelial activation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Prostaglandins</td>\n<td>Vasodilation, pain, fever</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Leukotrienes</td>\n<td>Increased vascular permeability, chemotaxis, leukocyte adhesion, and activation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cytokines (TNF, IL-1, IL-6)</td>\n<td>\n<p>Local: endothelial activation (expression of adhesion molecules).</p>\n<p>Systemic: fever, metabolic abnormalities, hypotension (shock)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Chemokines</td>\n<td>Chemotaxis, leukocyte activation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Platelet-activating factor</td>\n<td>Vasoconstriction, Vasodilation (at low concentration), increased vascular permeability, leukocyte adhesion, chemotaxis, degranulation, oxidative burst</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Complement</td>\n<td>Leukocyte chemotaxis and activation, direct target killing (membrane attack complex), vasodilation (mast cell stimulation)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kinins</td>\n<td>Increased vascular permeability, smooth muscle contraction, vasodilation, pain</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Note: Thromboxane A2 (TXA2) is a prostaglandin, which is a potent <strong>vasoconstrictor</strong></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(757, 'Pathology', 'PM1969. Principal Mediators of Inflammation and Their Source', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Mediator</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Source</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Histamine</td>\n<td>Mast cells, basophils, platelets</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Prostaglandins</td>\n<td>Mast cells, leukocytes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Leukotrienes</td>\n<td>Mast cells, leukocytes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cytokines (TNF, IL-1, IL-6)</td>\n<td>Macrophages, endothelial cells, mast cells</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Chemokines</td>\n<td>Leukocytes, activated macrophages</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Platelet-activating factor</td>\n<td>Leukocytes, mast cells</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Complement</td>\n<td>Plasma (produced in liver)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kinins</td>\n<td>Plasma (produced in liver)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(758, 'Pathology', 'PM1896. Mallory Bodies vs. Councilman Bodies', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Mallory bodies</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Councilman bodies</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Intra-cytoplasmic inclusions&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Acidophilic apoptotic bodies</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Due to aggregation of cytoskeletal intermediate filament</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Due to hepatocyte apoptosis&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 849\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Appears as clumped, amorphous, eosinophilic material within ballooned hepatocytes.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>Entire hepatocyte shrinks and appears as intense eosinophilic stained bodies</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Seen in</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Alcoholic hepatitis</li>\n<li>Primary biliary cholangitis&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Alpha-1 antitrypsin deficiency</li>\n<li>Indian childhood cirrhosis</li>\n<li>Hepatocellular carcinoma&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Seen in &nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Acute viral hepatitis</li>\n<li>Yellow fever</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p>Mallory bodies seen as clumped, amorphous eosinophilic material within ballooned hepatocytes</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/c3995e141b2f4a5fb51f696160da37e3x1280x1539.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\><p>Councilman bodies where the entire cell is shrunken into intense eosinophilic apoptotic body</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-2 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/e5db2e1403d1413ea08729154eb5cd37x1253x1026.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
