(1591, 'Medicine', 'PM1583. Treatment Goals for Adults with Diabetes', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p><strong>Index</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\189\>\n<p><strong>Goal</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>HbA1c*</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\189\>\n<p>&lt; 7 %</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>Preprandial capillary plasma glucose</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\189\>\n<p>80–130 mg/dL</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>Peak postprandial capillary plasma glucose</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\189\>\n<p>&lt;180 mg/dL</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>Blood pressure<sup>+</sup></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\189\>\n<p>&lt; 140/80 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Note that most diabetes associations recommend the target HbA1c must be individualized to the patient. A target of &lt;7% is reasonable in most individuals.</p>\n<p>+ Blood pressure: Harrisons 20th&nbsp; edition,(based on ADA) recommends the target blood pressure goal of &lt;140/90 mmHg for adults with diabetes. It further adds that for younger individuals the target blood pressure is &lt;130/80 mmHg. But the \AHA/SPRINT TRIAL recommendations\ recommend that the goal of blood pressure in patients with diabetes mellitus is less than <span class=\nowrap\>130/80</span> mmHg.</p>\n<p>Dyslipidemia: Although not a treatment goal, ADA recommends&nbsp;to intensify lifestyle therapy and optimize glycemic control for patients with elevated triglyceride levels (≥150 mg/dL [1.7 mmol/L]) and/or low HDL cholesterol (&lt;40 mg/dL for men, &lt;50 mg/dL&nbsp; for women). Treatment with statins would depend on the overall cardiovascular risk (ASCVD) rather than specific LDL/HDL cholesterol level.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1592, 'Medicine', 'PM1582. Comparative Features of Diabetic Ketoacidosis and Hyperglycemic Hyperosmolar State', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p><strong>DKA</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p><strong>HHS</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Seen in </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Type 1 DM</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>Type 2 DM</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Clinical features</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Abdominal pain</p>\n<p>Kussmaul respiration</p>\n<p>Fruity odour of breath</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>Altered sensorium</p>\n<p>Coma</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Glucose (mg/dL)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>250–600</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>600–1200</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Sodium</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>120–125</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>135–145</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Osmolality </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>300–320</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>330–380</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Plasma Ketones</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>++++</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>+/-</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Serum Bicarbonate</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>&lt; 15 meq/ L</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>Normal to slightly ↓</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Arterial pH </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>6.8–7.3</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>&gt;7.3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Arterial pCO<sub>2 </sub>(mmHg)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>20–30</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>Normal</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\169\>\n<p><strong>Anion Gap</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p><strong>↑</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\160\>\n<p>Normal to slightly ↑</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1593, 'Medicine', 'PM1550. Initial Tests for Diagnosing Cushings Syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>These include two steps:</p>\n<p><strong>1. Tests to detect hypercortisolism</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Midnight salivary or serum cortisol</strong> (highly sensitive test):<strong>&nbsp;</strong>The presence of cortisol in the saliva or serum at midnight signifies loss of diurnal variation of cortisol</li>\n<li><strong>24-hour urinary free cortisol excretion</strong>:&nbsp;Increased three times the normal value</li>\n<li><strong>Overnight dexamethasone suppression test</strong> (DST):&nbsp;Plasma cortisol &gt;1.8 μg/dL at 8 a.m after overnight exposure to dexamethasone (1 mg given at 11 p.m)</li>\n<li><strong>Low dose DST</strong> (highly specific test):&nbsp;Plasma cortisol &gt;1.8 μg/dL at 8 a.m. on the third day after giving 0.5 mg dexamethasone every 6 hours for 2 days</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>2. Test </strong><strong>to rule out pseudo Cushings syndrome</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Low-dose DST + CRH stimulation test</strong>: Plasma cortisol levels are increased in true Cushing’s but remain unaffected in pseudo Cushings.&nbsp;Dexa-induced negative feedback is overcome by CRH in true Cushing’s.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1594, 'Medicine', 'PM1549. Causes of Cushings Syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Exogenous causes </strong>(iatrogenic)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Prolonged administration of glucocorticoids (most common cause of Cushings)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Endogenous causes</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>ACTH independent </strong>(primary hypercortisolism)\n<ul>\n<li>Adrenocortical adenoma&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Adrenocortical carcinoma&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Bilateral adrenal hyperplasia</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>ACTH dependent&nbsp;</strong>(secondary hypercortisolism)\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cushing’s disease:&nbsp;</strong>ACTH secreting&nbsp;<strong>pituitary adenoma </strong>(most common cause of endogenous Cushings)</li>\n<li><strong>Paraneoplastic causes: </strong>Ectopic ACTH secreting tumors\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Small-cell lung carcinoma</strong></li>\n<li>Bronchial or pancreatic carcinoid tumors</li>\n<li>Medullary thyroid carcinoma</li>\n<li>Pheochromocytoma</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Rare causes</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Macronodular adrenal hyperplasia</li>\n<li>Primary pigmented nodular adrenal disease</li>\n<li>McCune <strong>–</strong> Albright syndrome</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1595, 'Medicine', 'PM1536. Water Deprivation test in Diabetes Insipidus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Procedure</strong>: Start the test at 4 am by checking the baseline urine osmolality. Deprive the patient of water till 12 pm (8 hours), and then re-check urine osmolality.&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/4fbb612d53a844a481418c1744026250x1200x1255.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Urine osmolality&nbsp;before water deprivation</td>\n<td>Urine osmolality after water deprivation</td>\n<td>Urine osmolality after desmopressin administration</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Normal&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Normal&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Increases</td>\n<td>No change</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Central DI</td>\n<td>Low</td>\n<td>No change</td>\n<td>&gt;50% increase from baseline</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nephrogenic DI</td>\n<td>Low</td>\n<td>No change</td>\n<td>&lt;10% increase from baseline</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Primary polydipsia</td>\n<td>Low</td>\n<td>Increases</td>\n<td>No change</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>Note: Normal urine osmolality- 500-850 mOsm/L<br><br></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1596, 'Medicine', 'PM1535. Causes of Nephrogenic DI', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>&nbsp;Drugs\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Lithium</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Amphotericin B</strong></li>\n<li>Demeclocycline</li>\n<li>Cisplatin</li>\n<li>Aminoglycosides</li>\n<li>Foscarnet</li>\n<li>Methoxyflurane</li>\n<li>Rifampin</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Genetic\n<ul>\n<li>X-linked recessive (AVP receptor-2 gene)</li>\n<li>Autosomal recessive (AQP2 gene)</li>\n<li>Autosomal dominant (AQP2 gene)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Metabolic\n<ul>\n<li>Hypercalcemia, hypercalciuria</li>\n<li>Hypokalemia</li>\n<li>Hyperoxaluria</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Sarcoidosis</li>\n<li>Sjogren syndrome</li>\n<li>Polycystic kidney disease</li>\n<li>Amyloidosis</li>\n<li>Vascular\n<ul>\n<li>Sickle cell disease and trait</li>\n<li>Ischemia (acute tubular necrosis)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Idiopathic</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1597, 'Medicine', 'PM1534. Causes of Central Diabetes insipidus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>Neoplasms:<strong>&nbsp;</strong>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\2\><strong>Pituitary adenomas</strong> (most common)</li>\n<li aria-level=\2\>Meningioma</li>\n<li aria-level=\2\>Metastasis from lung and breast cancers</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Infiltrative:&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>Sarcoidosis</li>\n<li>Langerhans cell histiocytosis</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Genetic:&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>Wolfram syndrome</li>\n<li>Hand-Schuller-Christian disease&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Infections:&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>Chronic meningitis</li>\n<li>Viral encephalitis</li>\n<li>Toxoplasmosis</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Inflammatory:\n<ul>\n<li>Granulomatosis with polyangiitis</li>\n<li>Lupus erythematosus</li>\n<li>Scleroderma</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Vascular:\n<ul>\n<li>Sheehan’s syndrome</li>\n<li>Aneurysm (internal carotid)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Head injury (closed and penetrating) including pituitary surgery</li>\n<li>Snakebite</li>\n<li>Lymphocytic hypophysitis</li>\n<li></li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1598, 'Medicine', 'PM1525. Tests for Acromegaly', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Screening test</strong>:</p>\n<p>The <strong>single</strong>&nbsp;best test for the diagnosis of acromegaly is the measurement of serum insulin-like growth factor-1 (<strong>IGF-1</strong>). A normal serum IGF-1 concentration is strong evidence that the patient does&nbsp;<strong>not</strong>&nbsp;have acromegaly.</p>\n<p><strong>Confirmatory test</strong>:</p>\n<p>GH suppression test:<strong>&nbsp;75 g</strong> of <strong>oral glucose</strong> (OGTT- oral glucose tolerance test) is administered to the patient. Blood GH levels are checked at 30, 60, 90, 120 min (i.e over 2 hours) after the glucose load.&nbsp;Normally, glucose suppresses GH and it falls to &lt;1 ng/mL. If GH <strong>&gt;1 ng/mL</strong>, it is diagnostic of acromegaly.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1599, 'Medicine,', 'PM1524. Diagnostic tests in Zollinger Ellison Syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>To confirm the diagnosis of ZES,</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Gastric pH &lt;2.5</strong> and</li>\n<li><strong>Serum gastrin &gt;1000pg/ml</strong> (normal &lt;100pg/ml)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Provocative tests can be done like the <strong>secretin stimulation test</strong> when the diagnosis is in doubt. An <strong>increase in serum gastrin &gt;200pg/ml</strong> following an IV bolus of secretin (2U/kg) is diagnostic.</p>\n<p>Other tests:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>BAO &gt;15mEq/h</strong> (or &gt;5mEq/h if they have had a procedure for peptic ulcer)</li>\n<li><strong>BAO: MAO ratio </strong>is <strong>increased </strong>(<strong>&gt;0.6</strong>)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>(BAO=Basal acid output; MAO=Maximal acid output)</p>\n<p>For localization</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Initial investigation - CT or MRI</li>\n<li>Best investigation - <strong>Endoscopic ultrasound</strong></li>\n<li>If the tumor is not localized - <strong>Somatostatin receptor scintigraphy</strong>.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1600, 'Medicine', 'PM1141. Rule of Tens in Pheochromocytoma', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Rule of 10s in Pheochromocytoma includes :</p>\n<ul>\n<li>10% are bilateral</li>\n<li>10% are extra- adrenal</li>\n<li>10% are malignant</li>\n<li>25-33 % are inherited.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note: Symptomatic patients do not follow the Rule of 10s</p>\n<div class=\section\>&nbsp;</div></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1601, 'Medicine', 'PM1140. Clinical features of Pheochromocytoma (By frequency of occurrence)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>Classical triad of symptoms:\n<ul>\n<li>Headaches – most common symptom</li>\n<li>Profuse sweating</li>\n<li>Palpitations and tachycardia</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Hypertension (sustained or intermittent) – most common&nbsp;sign</li>\n<li>Anxiety,&nbsp;panic attacks</li>\n<li>Hyperglycemia</li>\n<li>Hypercalcemia</li>\n<li>Pallor - due to&nbsp;alpha-1 mediated vasoconstriction</li>\n<li>Polyuria and polydipsia&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Orthostatic hypotension</li>\n<li>Dilated cardiomyopathy</li>\n<li>Erythrocytosis, high hematocrit (hemoconcentration)</li>\n<li>Constipation</li>\n<li>Abdominal pain</li>\n<li>Weakness</li>\n<li>Weight loss</li>\n<li>Nausea</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1602, 'Medicine', 'PM0992. Dawn Phenomenon and Somogyi Phenomenon', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\188\>\n<p><strong>Dawn phenomenon</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\255\>\n<p><strong>Somogyi phenomenon</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\188\>\n<p>Early morning <strong>hyperglycaemia</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\255\>\n<p>Early morning <strong>hyperglycaemia</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\188\>\n<p><strong>Normal blood glucose </strong>levels at 3 am</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\255\>\n<p><strong>Hypoglycaemia</strong> at 3 am</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p><strong>Mechanism</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\188\>\n<p>Early morning surge in growth hormone and cortisol which causes hyperglycemia</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\255\>\n<p>Excessive night basal insulin dose &gt; hypoglycemia in middle of night &gt; triggers the release of counterregulatory hormones which causes hyperglycemia.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p><strong>Treatment </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\188\>\n<p><strong>Increase</strong> nighttime long-acting insulin dose</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\255\>\n<p><strong>Decrease</strong> night time long-acting insulin dose</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1603, 'Medicine', 'PM0990. Abnormal Glucose Homeostasis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Individuals without overt diabetes can have <strong>abnormal glucose homeostasis.&nbsp;</strong>It is also&nbsp;called <strong>prediabetes</strong> or intermediate hyperglycemia. These people are at an increased risk of developing diabetes<strong>&nbsp;</strong>mellitus. Three categories of abnormal glucose homeostasis have been defined:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\bulletIndent2\>Impaired glucose tolerance&nbsp;(IGT) –&nbsp;blood glucose levels between 140 and 199 mg/dL following an oral glucose challenge</li>\n<li class=\bulletIndent2\>Impaired fasting glucose&nbsp;(IFG) – fasting<strong>&nbsp;</strong>blood glucose 100 to 125&nbsp;<span class=\nowrap\>mg/dL</span>&nbsp;</li>\n<li class=\bulletIndent2\>HbA1c&nbsp;– 5.7-6.4%</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\bulletIndent2\>Please&nbsp;note that impaired glucose tolerance and impaired fasting glucose are two distinct entities.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1604, 'Medicine', 'PM0989. ADA criteria for Diagnosis of Diabetes mellitus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Any one</strong> of the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Symptoms</strong> of diabetes <strong>plus</strong> Random Blood Glucose concentration <strong>≥</strong> <strong>200 mg/dL.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Fasting plasma</strong> glucose <strong>≥</strong> <strong>126 </strong>mg/dL.&nbsp;Fasting is defined as no caloric intake for at least 8 hours.</li>\n<li>Haemoglobin <strong>A1c </strong><strong>≥6.</strong><strong>5%</strong></li>\n<li><strong>2-hour</strong> plasma <strong>glucose </strong><strong>≥</strong> <strong>200 mg/dL</strong> during an <strong>oral glucose tolerance test.</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Note: In the absence of unequivocal hyperglycemia and acute metabolic decompensation, these criteria should be <strong>confirmed by repeat testing</strong> on a different day.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1605, 'Medicine', 'PM0988. Comparative Features between MODY and Type 2 DM', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\0\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Type 2 DM</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>MODY</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Age of onset</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Predominantly middle to old age</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Predominantly young (&lt; 25 years)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Pathology</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Beta cell dysfunction</p>\n<p>Insulin resistance</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Only Beta cell dysfunction</p>\n<p>No insulin resistance</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Family history</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Positive</p>\n<p>Inheritance - Polygenic&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vertical transmission through <strong>successive generations</strong> is <strong>not essential </strong>for diagnosis</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Positive</p>\n<p>Inheritance – Monogenic / <strong>Autosomal dominant</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Vertical transmission through at <strong>least two successive generation</strong> (ideally three) is <strong>essential</strong> for diagnosis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Insulin dependence</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Non-insulin dependent</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Non-insulin dependent</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Obesity</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Common</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Uncommon</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>DKA</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Uncommon</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Uncommon</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p><strong>Serum insulin level</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>High</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\206\>\n<p>Low</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1606, 'Medicine', 'PM0987. Comparative Features of Type I and Type II Diabetes mellitus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p><strong>Type 1 DM</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p><strong>Type 2 DM</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Etiology</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>Autoimmune</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Insulin resistance which later leads to impaired insulin secretion</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Age at onset</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>Usually young children</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Adult</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>HLA association</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p><strong>DR3, DR4</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>No HLA association</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Body weight</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>Normal / Underweight</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p><strong>Obese</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Family history</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>May or may not be positive</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Usually<strong> strongly positive</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Presentation</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>Abrupt</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Gradual or symptomatic</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Insulin requirement</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>Absolute</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Oral hypoglycemics, later insulin</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>Serum insulin level / C peptide level</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p>Low</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>High</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\155\>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Clinical Features</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\211\>\n<p><strong>Diabetic ketoacidosis</strong> is common&nbsp;</p>\n<p>It is associated with other autoimmune diseases like:</p>\n<p><strong>Thyroid disorders</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Addisons disease</li>\n<li>Rheumatoid arthritis</li>\n<li>Schmidt syndrome/ Polyglandular failure syndrome</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p><strong>Non-ketotic hyperosmolar coma</strong> is common</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1607, 'Medicine', 'PM0986. Types of Diabetes mellitus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>I. <strong>Type 1 diabetes</strong>:<strong>&nbsp;</strong>Beta cell destruction, usually leading to absolute insulin deficiency</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Immune-mediated</li>\n<li>Idiopathic</li>\n</ul>\n<p>II. <strong>Type 2 diabetes</strong>: Insulin resistance with relative insulin deficiency</p>\n<p>III.&nbsp;<strong>Other specific types</strong> of diabetes</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Genetic defects of beta cell development or function\n<ul>\n<li><strong>MODY – </strong>Maturity Onset Diabetes of Young</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Genetic defects in insulin action\n<ul>\n<li>Type A insulin resistance</li>\n<li>Leprechaunism</li>\n<li>Rabson-Mendenhall syndrome Lipodystrophy syndromes</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Diseases of the exocrine pancreas\n<ul>\n<li>Pancreatitis</li>\n<li>Neoplasia</li>\n<li>Cystic fibrosis</li>\n<li>Hemochromatosis</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Endocrinopathies\n<ul>\n<li>Acromegaly</li>\n<li>Cushing’s syndrome</li>\n<li>Glucagonoma</li>\n<li>Pheochromocytoma</li>\n<li>Hyperthyroidism</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Infections\n<ul>\n<li>Congenital rubella</li>\n<li>Cytomegalovirus</li>\n<li>Coxsackievirus</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Uncommon forms of immune-mediated diabetes\n<ul>\n<li>“Stiff-person” syndrome</li>\n<li>Anti-insulin receptor antibodies</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Genetic syndromes sometimes associated with diabetes\n<ul>\n<li>Wolfram’s syndrome</li>\n<li>Down’s syndrome, Klinefelter’s syndrome, Turner’s syndrome</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>IV.<strong> Gestational diabetes mellitus (GDM)</strong></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1608, 'Medicine,', 'PM0929. Causes of Male Infertility', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Pre-testicular causes:</strong></p>\n<p>Endocrine cause</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Gonadotropin deficiency</li>\n<li>Thyroid dysfunction</li>\n<li>Hyperprolactinemia</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Psychosexual</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Impotence</li>\n<li>Erectile dysfunction</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Drugs</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Antihypertensives</li>\n<li>Antipsychotics</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Genetics</p>\n<ul>\n<li>47XXY</li>\n<li>Y chromosome deletions</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Testicular causes:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Immotile cilia syndrome</li>\n<li>Cryptorchidism</li>\n<li>Orchitis (mumps, Tb, gonorrhoea, traumatic)</li>\n<li>Toxins(Drugs,radiation)</li>\n<li>Primary testicular failure</li>\n<li>Sertoli cell-only syndrome</li>\n<li>Oligoasthenoteratozoospermia</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Post-testicular causes:</strong></p>\n<p>Obstruction of efferent duct&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Congenital</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Absence of Vas deferens</li>\n<li>Youngs syndrome</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Acquired (Inflammatory block)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Tuberculosis</li>\n<li>Gonorrhea</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Surgical</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vasectomy</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Others</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Ejaculatory failure</li>\n<li>Bladder neck surgery</li>\n<li>Retrograde ejaculation&nbsp;</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1609, 'Medicine,', 'PM0786. Causes of Hypothyroidism', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Primary </strong></p>\n<p>(Low T3, T4 → Raised TSH levels)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Secondary</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong>(Low TSH levels → Low T3, T4)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Tertiary</strong></p>\n<p><strong> </strong>(Low TRH → Low TSH → Low T3,T4)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Hashimoto’s thyroiditis</strong></p>\n<p>RAI therapy for Grave’s disease</p>\n<p>Post thyroidectomy</p>\n<p>Excessive iodine intake - Wolff Chiakoff effect</p>\n<p>Subacute thyroiditis</p>\n<p>Medications: Antithyroid drugs, lithium</p>\n<p>Iodine deficiency, dyshormonogenesis</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Pituitary tumour</strong></p>\n<p>Pituitary resection or ablation</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Hypothalamic insufficiency</strong></p>\n<p>Resistance to thyroid hormone</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1610, 'Surgery,', 'PM0784. Thyroid storm / Thyrotoxic crisis:', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>It is an emergency caused by an acute exacerbation of hyperthyroidism.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Precipitating factors:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>When a thyrotoxic patient has been<strong> inadequately prepared for thyroidectomy</strong></li>\n<li>Abrupt cessation of antithyroid medications</li>\n<li>Stress\n<ul>\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Thyroid or non-thyroid surgery</li>\n<li>Trauma in patients with untreated thyrotoxicosis</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Acute iodine load\n<ul>\n<li>Amiodarone administration&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Exposure to iodinated contrast agents</li>\n<li>Following RAI therapy</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Clinical features:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Fever</li>\n<li>Tachycardia</li>\n<li>Altered mentation (delirium, psychosis, coma)</li>\n<li>GI symptoms (nausea, vomiting, diarrhoea)</li>\n<li><strong>Atrial fibrillation</strong> and <strong>cardiac failure</strong> - most common causes of death</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Treatment of thyroid storm:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Treatment modality</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>IV Fluids, ice packs</td>\n<td>Rehydration and external cooling</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Propylthiouracil</strong><br><strong>(DOC)</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Reduces peripheral T4 to T3 conversion</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Propranolol</td>\n<td>\n<p>Block adrenergic effects</p>\n<p>Reduces peripheral T4 to T3 conversion</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Corticosteroids</td>\n<td>\n<p>Inhibits the release of thyroid hormone from the gland</p>\n<p>Reduces peripheral T4 to T3 conversion</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lugol’s iodine/ sodium ipodate</td>\n<td>Inhibits the release of thyroid hormone from the gland</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Digoxin</td>\n<td>Controls the associated atrial fibrillation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diuretics and administration of oxygen</td>\n<td>\n<p>To manage cardiac failure</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1611, 'Medicine', 'PM0122. Antibodies seen in some autoimmune thyroid disorders', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Antibody</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Disorder</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>TSH receptor-stimulating Immunoglobulins (TSI)</td>\n<td>Graves disease</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti TPO &amp; Anti Tg antibodies</td>\n<td>Chronic lymphocytic(Hashimoto) thyroiditis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>TRBAb</p>\n<p>(maternal transmission)</p>\n</td>\n<td>Transient congenital hypothyroidism (maternal autoimmune thyroid disease)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li>Anti TPO – Anti thyroperoxidase antibody</li>\n<li>Anti Tg – Antithyroglobulin antibody</li>\n<li>TRBAb – TSH receptor blocking antibodies</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1612, 'Medicine', 'PM2432. Maddrey score', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Maddrey score or DF score:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>DF =&nbsp;4.6 X (the prolongation of the prothrombin time above control [seconds]) + serum bilirubin (mg/dL)</li>\n<li>To assess the prognosis in alcoholic hepatitis.</li>\n<li>DF ≥ 32 is severe disease&nbsp; and is an indication for starting glucocorticoids.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1613, 'Medicine,', 'PM2163. Indications of liver transplantation', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Adult</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Children</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Non-cholestatic (65%)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Viral hepatitis B and C</li>\n<li>Alcoholic liver cirrhosis</li>\n<li>Cryptogenic</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Cholestatic (14%)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Primary biliary cirrhosis</li>\n<li>Primary sclerosing cholangitis</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Autoimmune (5%)</p>\n<p>Malignant neoplasm (2%)</p>\n<p>Miscellaneous (14%)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Biliary atresia (58%)</p>\n<p>Inborn errors of metabolism (11%)</p>\n<p>Cholestatic (9%)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Primary sclerosing cholangitis</li>\n<li>Alagille syndrome</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Autoimmune (4%)</p>\n<p>Viral hepatitis (2%)</p>\n<p>Miscellaneous (16%)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1614, 'Medicine', 'PM2049. Serum Ascites Albumin Gradient  (SAAG)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The serum ascites albumin gradient is calculated as follows:</p>\n<p>SAAG = Serum albumin - Ascitic fluid albumin</p>\n<p>It can be used to determine the cause of ascites following ascitic fluid analysis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/08ad7499e5e74b398f3c98a430c6af02x1200x1361.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1615, 'Medicine', 'PM2048. Causes of Portal Hypertension', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/ba11a261470c410298f73941ff987a2fx1280x2190.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1616, 'Medicine', 'PM1985. Drugs causing acute Pancreatitis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Group</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Examples</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors</td>\n<td>\n<p>Captopril</p>\n<p>Lisinopril</p>\n<p>Enalapril</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Angiotensin receptor inhibitor</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Losartan</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antimicrobial</td>\n<td>\n<p>Erythromycin</p>\n<p>Isoniazid</p>\n<p>Metronidazole</p>\n<p>Sulfamethazine</p>\n<p>Sulfamethoxazole</p>\n<p>Tetracycline</p>\n<p>Dapsone</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antithyroid</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Carbimazole</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>H2 blocker</td>\n<td>\n<p>Cimetidine</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antipsychotics</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Clozapine</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antiepileptic</td>\n<td>\n<p>Valproic acid</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Steroids&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Dexamethasone</p>\n<p>Hydrocortisone</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diuretics&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Furosemide</p>\n<p>Hydrochlorothiazide</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lipid-lowering drugs&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Simvastatin</li>\n<li>Fluvastatin</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hormones</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Estrogen&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Stibogluconate</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anticancer drugs</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>5-Aminosalicylic acid compounds</li>\n<li>L-Asparaginase</li>\n<li>Azathioprine</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Others</td>\n<td>\n<p>Acetaminophen</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1617, 'Medicine', 'PM1934. Differences between primary sclerosing cholangitis (PSC)  and primary biliary cholangitis (PBC)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Primary Biliary Cholangitis</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Primary Sclerosing Cholangitis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antibodies</td>\n<td>\n<p>Antimitochondrial antibodies positive in most patients</p>\n<p>Antinuclear antibodies positive</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 860\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Antimitochondrial antibodies /AMA typically negative</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p><strong>p-ANCA</strong>-positive</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Age group</td>\n<td>40–60 years</td>\n<td>30-45 years</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gender predominance</td>\n<td>Females</td>\n<td>Males</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Site</td>\n<td>Intrahepatic&nbsp;bile ducts only</td>\n<td>Intra- and extrahepatic bile ducts</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;Associated with</td>\n<td>\n<p>Sjogren syndrome</p>\n<p>Hashimotos thyroiditis&nbsp;</p>\n<p>CREST&nbsp;syndrome</p>\n<p>Rheumatoid arthritis</p>\n<p>Celiac disease</p>\n</td>\n<td><strong>Ulcerative colitis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diagnosis</td>\n<td>Biopsy</td>\n<td>MRCP/ERCP-strictures&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Biopsy findings</td>\n<td>&nbsp;<strong>Florid duct lesion</strong> (granuloma)</td>\n<td>Concentric \<strong>onion-skin\</strong>&nbsp;fibrosis &nbsp; &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Long-term complication</td>\n<td>Cirrhosis</td>\n<td>\n<p>Cirrhosis</p>\n<p>Cholangiocarcinoma</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1618, 'Medicine', 'PM1931. Types of acute  liver failure', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Condition&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Time</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Cerebral edema&nbsp;</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td><strong>Causes</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hyperacute liver failure</td>\n<td>&nbsp;7 days or less</td>\n<td>Common&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Viral<br>paracetamol</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Acute liver faliure</td>\n<td>&nbsp;8 to 28 days</td>\n<td>Common</td>\n<td>Cryptogenic<br>drugs</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Subacute liver failure</td>\n<td>&nbsp;4 to 24 weeks</td>\n<td>Uncommon</td>\n<td>Cryptogenic<br>drugs</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><span>Time: onset of jaundice to&nbsp; encephalopathy</span></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1619, 'Medicine', 'PM1902. Extrahepatic Manifestations of Hepatitis B and C', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Hepatitis B</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Hepatitis C</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hematological</td>\n<td>\n<p>Aplastic anemia</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Essential mixed cryoglobulinemia</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Renal</td>\n<td>\n<p>Membranous glomerulonephritis (hepatitis B &gt; C)</p>\n<p>Membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis</p>\n<p>Membranous glomerulonephritis &nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vascular</td>\n<td>\n<p>Polyarteritis nodosa (hepatitis B&gt;C)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Leukocytoclastic vasculitis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dermatologic</td>\n<td>\n<p>Erythema multiforme (Hepatitis B&gt;C)</p>\n<p>Urticaria</p>\n<p>Serum sickness</p>\n<p>Infantile papular acrodermatitis (Gianotti–Crosti syndrome)</p>\n<p>Erythema nodosum</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Erythema multiforme</p>\n<p>Sporadic porphyria cutanea tarda</p>\n<p>Lichen planus</p>\n<p>Necrolytic acral erythema</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Hepatitis C also increases the risk of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Non-Hodgkin’s lymphoma</li>\n<li>Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura</li>\n<li>Autoimmune hemolytic anemia</li>\n<li>Diabetes mellitus</li>\n<li>Autoimmune thyroiditis &nbsp;</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1620, 'Medicine', 'PM1881. Rotor syndrome vs Dubin johnson syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Rotor syndrome</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Dubin Johnson syndrome</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Inheritance</td>\n<td>Autosomal recessive</td>\n<td>Autosomal recessive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Defect</td>\n<td>Organic anion transporting polypeptide &nbsp;defect.(OATP1B1,OATP1B3)</td>\n<td>Multi drug resistance protein (MRP )2 mutation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Kernicterus</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Biopsy</td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n<td>Black pigmentation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Total Urinary &nbsp;coproporphyrin</td>\n<td>Elevated</td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Urinary &nbsp;coproporphyrin I</td>\n<td>&lt;70%</td>\n<td>&gt;80%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bromsulphalein clearance test</td>\n<td>Slow clearance</td>\n<td>No/Delayed clearance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gall bladder on oral cholangiography</td>\n<td>Visualized</td>\n<td>Not visualized</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cholestasis</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Serum bile acids</td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Jaundice</td>\n<td>Mild (TB&lt;4mg/dl)</td>\n<td>Mild (TB&lt;4mg/dl)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1621, 'Medicine', 'PM1855. Diagnostic criteria for Clostridium difficile infection', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The diagnosis of CDI is based on a combination of clinical criteria:</p>\n<p>1.Diarrhea (≥3 unformed stools per 24 h for ≥2 days) with no other recognized cause&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>2.Detection of toxins A or B in the stool by PCR or culture</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;or &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Detection of pseudomembranes in the colon</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1622, 'Medicine', 'PM1854. Investigations in  Malabsorption Syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The following are the general tests for malabsorption:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Disorder</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Investigation</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fat malabsorption</td>\n<td>\n<p>Quantitative: 24h fecal fat &gt;7g</p>\n<p>Qualitative: Sudan III staining</p>\n<p>C<sup>14</sup> Triolein breath test</p>\n<p>Fecal steatocrit</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Carbohydrate malabsorption</td>\n<td>\n<p>D-xylose test</p>\n<p>Lactose hydrogen breath test</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Protein malabsorption</td>\n<td>C<sup>13</sup> egg-white breath test</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The following are the specific tests for malabsorption:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Disorder</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Investigation</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Celiac disease</td>\n<td>\n<p>Anti-tissue transglutaminase (anti-tTG)</p>\n<p>Anti-endomysial antibodies</p>\n<p>Mucosal biopsy showing villous atrophy, crypt hyperplasia, lamina propria infiltrates, and normal mucosal thickness.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Whipples disease</td>\n<td>Mucosal biopsy showing PAS +ve macrophages in lamina propria</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pancreatic insufficiency</td>\n<td>\n<p>Fecal elastase</p>\n<p>Fecal chymotrypsin</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Small intestinal bacterial overgrowth (SIBO)</td>\n<td>\n<p>Due to Enterobacter or Pseudomonas - jejunal aspirate&nbsp;&gt;10<sup>3</sup>&nbsp;CFU</p>\n<p>Due to other organisms - jejunal aspirate&nbsp;&gt;10<sup>5</sup> CFU</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1623, 'Medicine', 'PM1853. Types of Chronic gastritis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Type A and Type B</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Type B (90% cases)</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Type A (10% cases)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Association</strong></td>\n<td><em>Helicobacter&nbsp;pylori</em></td>\n<td>\n<p>Autoimmune disease</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Site</strong></td>\n<td>Antral Predominant</td>\n<td>Fundus and body with antral sparing</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Acid Production</strong></td>\n<td>Normal to increased</td>\n<td>Decreased (<strong>achlorhydria)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Gastrin</strong></td>\n<td>Normal to increased</td>\n<td>Increased <strong>(hypergastrinemia)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>HLA</strong></td>\n<td>No association</td>\n<td>HLA DR3, HLA B8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Serology</strong></td>\n<td>Antibodies to <em>H. pylori</em></td>\n<td>\n<p>Sensitive: Anti-parietal antibodies</p>\n<p>Specific: Anti-IF antibodies</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Cytokines involved</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>IL-1, IL-8</p>\n</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Long term sequelae</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Non-atrophic pan gastritis- MALTOMA</p>\n<p>Atrophic pan gastritis-Adenocarcinoma</p>\n<p>Peptic ulcer</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Diffuse atrophy,</p>\n<p>Pernicious anemia,</p>\n<p>Adenocarcinoma,</p>\n<p>Gastric carcinoid tumors</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Histology</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Intraepithelial neutrophils,</p>\n<p>Subepithelial plasma cells</p>\n</td>\n<td>Lymphocytes, plasma cells,&nbsp;and macrophages</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Other associated lesion</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Hyperplastic/inflammatory polyps</p>\n</td>\n<td>Neuroendocrine hyperplasia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Association</strong></td>\n<td>Low socioeconomic&nbsp;status, poverty,&nbsp;residence in rural areas</td>\n<td>Autoimmune diseases like&nbsp;thyroiditis, diabetes&nbsp;mellitus, Graves disease</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->');
INSERT INTO db_pearl_m (pid, subject, pearl_title, pearl_desc) VALUES
(1624, 'Medicine,', 'PM1852. Endoscopic Findings in Esophagitis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Conditions</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Endoscopic findings</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Infectious esophagitis</td>\n<td>Diffuse and involve the proximal esophagus &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>HSV esophagitis</td>\n<td>Vesicles and small punched-out lesions (volcano ulcers)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>CMV&nbsp;esophagitis</td>\n<td>Serpiginous ulcers</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Peptic esophagitis</td>\n<td>Solitary and distal &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Eosinophilic esophagitis</td>\n<td>Multiple esophageal rings, linear furrows, or white punctate exudates (feline esophagus)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pill esophagitis</td>\n<td>Singular and deep at points of luminal narrowing with sparing of the distal esophagus</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Candida esophagitis</td>\n<td>White friable plaques, in advance form - adherent, grey-white pseudomembranes.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The image below shows the lesions of CMV esophagitis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/4d3459a16bb04e7db0a37697b70d64f3x358x327.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The image below shows the lesions of candida esophagitis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/27753ea663e94016878e0fdfbfe7ab80x526x488.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The image below shows feline esophagus in eosinophilic esophagitis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/fd7fb7a1bf14483f9405672cd6b522dex592x472.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The image below shows the erosive lesion of pill esophagitis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/b7d3184539ba462d8fa7bfd006f20927x512x399.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The image below shows the lesions of HSV esophagitis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/6b4e6f9f77b44981b91065e60457a1e6x388x439.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1625, 'Medicine', 'PM1848. Inlammatory Bowel Disease (IBD): General One-Liners', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>FEATURE</td>\n<td>CAUSE/PRESENTATION</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Most common ophthalmic manifestation of IBD</td>\n<td>Uveitis and episcleritis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Most common ophthalmic manifestation correlate with relapse</td>\n<td>Episcleritis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Feature of arthritis in IBD (LAMP-P)</td>\n<td>Lower limb-asymmetric- migrating- peripheral-pauci-articular</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Correlate with early complication in CD</td>\n<td><br>\n<h3 class=\r\><span>Anti-<em>Saccharomyces cerevisiae</em> antibodies </span></h3>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Predict the response to surgery in CD</td>\n<td>Anti-I2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>No role in&nbsp; maintenance of IBD</td>\n<td>Steroids</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fecal antigen used in IBD</td>\n<td>Lactoferrin, Calprotectin</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gene involved in&nbsp; IBD</td>\n<td><em>NOD2</em>, Chr 16</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;CD- Crohns Disease</p>\n<p>IBD - Inflammatory Bowel Disease</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1626, 'Medicine', 'PM1847. Inflammatory Bowel Disease (IBD)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Crohns disease</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Ulcerative colitis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Age of onset&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>2nd-4th decades &amp; 7th-9th decades</td>\n<td>2nd-4th decades &amp; 7th-9th decades&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Most common presentation</strong></td>\n<td>Ileocolitis&nbsp;with rectal sparing</td>\n<td>Proctitis (rectum)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Protective factors</strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;None&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Smoking&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Appendicectomy</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Risk factors</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>OCP</p>\n<p>Smoking</p>\n<p>Antibiotic during first year of life&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>α-Methyldopa</p>\n<p>Antibiotic during first year of life</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>T cell involved</strong></td>\n<td>TH1&nbsp;</td>\n<td>TH2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Gross findings/ endoscopic findings</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Transmural involvement</p>\n<p>Segmental involvement</p>\n<p>Skip lesions</p>\n<p>Cobblestone appearance</p>\n<p>Creeping fat</p>\n<p>Longitudinal ulcers</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Mucosal and superficial submucosal involvement&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Continuous involvement</p>\n<p>Pseudopolyps&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Backwash ileitis&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Collar button ulcers</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Earliest finding</strong></td>\n<td>Aphthous ulcer</td>\n<td>Erythematous mucosa with a fine granular surface</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Microscopic findings&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>Deep, knife-like ulcers</p>\n<p>Granulomas</p>\n<p>Pyloric metaplasia&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>Superficial, broad-based</p>\n<p>Cryptitis and crypt abscess&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Complications&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Fistulas&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Strictures</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Hemorrhage</p>\n<p>Toxic megacolon</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Recurrence after resection</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Common</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Uncommon, curative after resection</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Radiological findings&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Aphthous ulcer</p>\n<p>Rose thorn appearance</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Mucosal granularity</p>\n<p>Lead pipe appearance</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Extraintestinal manifestations</strong></td>\n<td colspan=\2\>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 807\>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 807\>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 807\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Episcleritis, uveitis&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Migratory polyarthritis</p>\n<p>Ankylosing spondylitis, sacroiliitis</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 807\>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 807\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Erythema nodosum</p>\n<p>Pyoderma gangrenosum- MC in UC</p>\n<p>Primary sclerosing cholangitis- MC in UC</p>\n<p>Renal Calculi- MC in CD</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br><br></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1627, 'Medicine,', 'PM1802. Glasgow-Blatchford score For UGI bleed', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>Total score ranges from <strong>0 to 23.</strong></li>\n<li>Hemoglobin value scores differs for men and women.</li>\n<li>Scores of <strong>6 or more</strong> were associated with a greater than <strong>50% risk of needing an intervention</strong>.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Factors</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Value</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Score</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Systolic blood pressure</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>100-109 mmHg</p>\n<p>90-99 mmHg</p>\n<p>&lt;90 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n<p>2</p>\n<p>3</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Blood urea nitrogen</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>6.5-7.9 mmol/L</strong></p>\n<p>8.0-9.9 mmol/L</p>\n<p>10.0-24.9 mmol/L</p>\n<p><strong>≥25 mmol/L</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>2</strong></p>\n<p>3</p>\n<p>4</p>\n<p><strong>6</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Haemoglobin for men</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>12.0-12.9 g/dl</p>\n<p><strong>10.0-11.9 g/dL</strong></p>\n<p><strong>10.0g/dL</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n<p><strong>3</strong></p>\n<p><strong>6</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Haemoglobin for women</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>&lt;10.0-11.9 g/dL</p>\n<p>&lt;10.0 g/dL</p>\n<p>Pulse&nbsp;≥100 beats/min</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n<p>6</p>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Other variable at presentation</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Melena</p>\n<p>Syncope</p>\n<p>Hepatic disease</p>\n<p>Cardiac failure</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n<p>2</p>\n<p>2</p>\n<p>2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1628, 'Surgery,', 'PM1633. Ranson Prognostic Criteria for Acute Pancreatitis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\471\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\3\><strong>Ransons prognostic criteria at presentation</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Parameter</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Non-gallstone pancreatitis</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Gallstone pancreatitis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Age</strong></td>\n<td>&gt;55 years</td>\n<td>&gt;70 years</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Blood glucose level</strong></td>\n<td>&gt;200 mg/dL</td>\n<td>&gt;220 mg/dL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>White blood cell count</strong></td>\n<td>&gt;16,000 cells/mm<sup>3</sup></td>\n<td>&gt;18,000 cells/mm<sup>3</sup></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Serum LDH level</strong></td>\n<td>&gt;350 IU/L</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&gt;400 IU/L</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Serum Aspartate aminotransferase level</strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;&gt;250 IU/L</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&gt;250 IU/L</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table width=\484\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\3\><strong>Ransons prognostic criteria after 48 hours of admission</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Parameter</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Non-gallstone pancreatitis</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Gallstone pancreatitis&nbsp;</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Hematocrit fall<br></strong></td>\n<td>&gt;10%</td>\n<td>&gt;10%</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Serum calcium level</strong></td>\n<td>&lt;8 mg/dL</td>\n<td>&lt;8 mg/dL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Base deficit</strong></td>\n<td>&gt;4 mEq/L</td>\n<td>&gt;5 mEq/L</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Blood urea nitrogen level increase&nbsp;<br></strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>≥5 mg/dL despite IV fluid hydration</p>\n</td>\n<td>≥2 mg/dL despite IV fluid hydration</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Fluid sequestration<br></strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;&gt;6 L</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&gt;4 L</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>PaO<sub>2</sub></strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;&lt;60 mm Hg</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Not available</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Ranson score<strong> ≥3</strong> defines <strong>severe pancreatitis</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Score Interpretation</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\half_rhythm\>\n<div>0 to 2 points: 0% to 3% mortality</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\half_rhythm\>\n<div>3 to 4 points: 15% mortality</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\half_rhythm\>\n<div>5 to 6 points: 40% mortality</div>\n</li>\n<li class=\half_rhythm\>\n<div>7 to 11: nearly 100% mortality</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1629, 'Medicine,', 'PM1603. Revised Model for End-stage liver disease  (MELD) scoring system: MELD 3.0', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>MELD 3.0 score has the following components (Mnemonic <strong>F BASIC</strong>)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Female sex</li>\n<li>Bilirubin</li>\n<li>Albumin</li>\n<li>Serum sodium (mEq/L)</li>\n<li>INR (International Normalized ratio)</li>\n<li>Creatinine</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Uses:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Predict short-term prognosis in patients undergoing transjugular intrahepatic portosystemic shunt (TIPS) insertion</li>\n<li>Assess and <strong>prioritize patients</strong> awaiting <strong>liver transplantation</strong></li>\n<li>Assess prognosis in cirrhosis</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\bulletIndent1\>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1630, 'Medicine,', 'PM1597. Difference between pyogenic and amebic liver abscess', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Clinical features</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Pyogenic abscess</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Amebic abscess</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Age</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>&gt;50 years</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>20–40 years</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Male:Female ratio</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1.5:1</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>10:1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Solitary vs multiple</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Solitary 50%</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Solitary 80%</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Location</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Right lobe</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Right lobe</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Travel to endemic area</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>No</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Alcohol</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Common</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Common</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Most common symptom</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Fever with chills</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Abdominal pain</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Most common lab abnormality</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Elevated ALP</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Elevated ALP</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Jaundice and elevated bilirubin</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>More common</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Less common</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Diagnosis</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Positive blood culture</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Positive antiamebic antibodies</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;ALP: alkaline phophatase</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1631, 'Medicine', 'PM1591. Nazer’s Prognostic Index', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Nazer’s prognostic index</strong> for <strong>Wilson’s disease</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Serum bilirubin</li>\n<li>Serum aspartate aminotransferase (AST)</li>\n<li>Prolongation of prothrombin time (sec)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Interpretation of Scores :</p>\n<ul>\n<li>&lt; 7 – Medical therapy</li>\n<li>7–9 – Clinical judgement, Either medical / surgical treatment</li>\n<li>&gt; 9 – Liver transplantation</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1632, 'Medicine', 'PM1545. Causes of Hyperamylasemia', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pancreatic Diseases</strong> <strong>&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp; Non-Pancreatic Disorders</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Other Abdominal</strong> <strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Disorders &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Acute pancreatitis</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Pancreatic pseudocyst</strong></li>\n<li>Ascites caused by pancreatic duct disruption</li>\n<li>Pancreatic necrosis, trauma, carcinoma</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Renal insufficiency</li>\n<li>Salivary gland lesions\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Mumps</strong></li>\n<li>Calculus</li>\n<li>Irradiation sialadenitis</li>\n<li>Maxillofacial surgery</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>CA lung/esophagus/breast/ovary</li>\n<li>Macroamylasemia</li>\n<li>Burns</li>\n<li><strong>DKA</strong></li>\n<li>Pregnancy</li>\n<li>Renal transplantation</li>\n<li>Cerebral trauma</li>\n<li>Drugs: opiates</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Biliary<strong> tract disease:&nbsp;</strong>cholecystitis, choledocholithiasis</li>\n<li>Intraabdominal disease\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Perforated/penetrating peptic ulcer</strong></li>\n<li>Intestinal obstruction or inflammation</li>\n<li><strong>Ruptured ectopic pregnancy</strong></li>\n<li>Peritonitis</li>\n<li>Aortic aneurysm</li>\n<li>Postoperative</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1633, 'Medicine', 'PM1539. Diagnostic Evaluation of the Bile Ducts', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Diagnostic Evaluation of the Bile Ducts</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Hepatobiliary ultrasound:</strong> Initial procedure of choice in investigating possible biliary tract obstruction</li>\n<li><strong>CT scan:</strong> Procedure of choice in investigating possible biliary obstruction if diagnostic limitations prevent HBUS</li>\n<li><strong>MRCP:</strong> Useful modality for visualizing pancreatic and biliary ducts</li>\n<li><strong>ERCP: Best visualisation of distal biliary tract</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Endoscopic sphincterotomy and stone removal can also be done</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>PTC(Percutaneous Transhepatic Cholangiography): Best visualisation of proximal biliary tract</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Indicated when ERCP is contraindicated or failed</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>EUS: </strong>Most sensitive method to <strong>detect ampullary stones</strong></li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1634, 'Medicine,', 'PM1538. Courvoisier’s Law', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Courvoisier’s Law</strong> states that the presence of a <strong>palpably enlarged gallbladder</strong> suggests that the <strong>biliary obstruction </strong>is secondary to an<strong> underlying malignancy </strong>rather than to calculous disease.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1635, 'Medicine,', 'PM1537. Diagnostic Evaluation of the Gall Bladder', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li><strong>Gallbladder Ultrasound: </strong>Investigation of choice for <strong>detection of gall stones</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Abdominal X-ray: </strong>Useful in&nbsp;\n<ul>\n<li>Calcified gall stones</li>\n<li>Emphysematous cholecystitis</li>\n<li>Porcelain gallbladder</li>\n<li>Limey bile</li>\n<li>Gallstone ileus</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Radioisotope scans </strong>(HIDA/DIDA/DISIDA)\n<ul>\n<li>Indicated for <strong>confirmation of suspected acute cholecystitis</strong></li>\n<li>Useful in diagnosis of <strong>acalculous cholecystopathy</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Abbreviations:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>HIDA: <strong>H</strong>epatobiliary <strong>I</strong>mino<strong>D</strong>iacetic <strong>A</strong>cid scan</li>\n<li>DIDA/DISDA: <strong>Di</strong>-i<strong>s</strong>opropyl <strong>I</strong>mino<strong>D</strong>iacetic <strong>A</strong>cid - Dynamic Tc99m DIDA Cholescintigraphy</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1636, 'Medicine', 'PM1532. Prerequisites for Medical Therapy in Cholelithiasis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li><strong>Functioning gallbladder</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Radiolucent stones</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Stones &lt;10mm</strong></li>\n<li><strong>Cholesterol stones </strong></li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1637, 'Surgery,', 'PM1528. Achalasia Cardia', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><div class=\page\ title=\Page 2599\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Achalasia cardia is a rare disease caused by the <strong>loss of ganglion cells</strong> within the esophageal myenteric plexus. <span>Their absence leads to </span><strong>increased tone of the lower esophageal sphincter</strong><span>,&nbsp;impaired relaxation of the lower&nbsp;esophageal sphincter (LES),&nbsp;and absent peristalsis.</span></p>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 2599\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Achalasia is the <strong>only true motility disorder</strong> of the&nbsp;esophagus.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Primary achalasia</strong> is due to ganglion cell degeneration and is thought to be due to an autoimmune process attributable to latent infection with human herpes simplex virus 1 (HSV1) combined with genetic susceptibility.</li>\n<li><strong>Secondary achalasia</strong> may arise in Chagas disease.</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<p>Clinical features:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Dysphagia</strong> <strong>(solid and liquid food)</strong></li>\n<li>Regurgitation</li>\n<li>Chest pain</li>\n<li>Weight loss</li>\n<li>Bronchitis, pneumonia, or lung abscess from aspiration</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Differential diagnosis: <strong>Diffuse esophageal spasm, pseudoachalasia</strong></p>\n<p>On barium swallow: <strong>Bird beak-appearance</strong></p>\n<p>Investigation of choice: <strong>Manometry (most sensitive)</strong></p>\n<p>Treatment: <strong>Pneumatic dilatation, Heller myotomy</strong></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/c90179ebbbca4cd090d07b3ae3029c74x319x598.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1638, 'Medicine,', 'PM1527. Zenker’s Diverticulum', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Zenkers diverticulum occurs due to <strong>herniation</strong> of mucosa and submucosa through the <strong>Killians triangle</strong>, which is a weak area between two&nbsp;parts of the <strong>inferior constrictor - </strong>(thyropharyngeus and cricopharyngeus)&nbsp;in the <strong>posterior pharyngeal wall.&nbsp;</strong>It is usually seen in elderly patients (&gt;60 years).</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/f1d91adec7cf4043844cb02f3d29e3ffx600x1200.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Characteristics</strong> of Zenkers diverticulum:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Hypopharyngeal</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>False diverticula - doesnt have a muscle coat</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Acquired&nbsp;</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Pulsion diverticulum&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Pathophysiology</strong>: Impaired relaxation and spasm of the cricopharyngeus muscle after swallowing can result in increased pressure within the distal pharynx, and cause the diverticulum.Clinical features:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Dysphagia</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Regurgitation</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Halitosis</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Aspiration</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Gurgling sound during swallowing</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The investigation of choice is <strong>barium swallow</strong> (lateral X-ray).</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/ae9cc93c02584eb8b4f68d0d17465135x515x727.GIF\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>It is treated with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Cricopharyngeal myotomy</strong></li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Surgical diverticulectomy</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Marsupialization</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Dohlman’s procedure</strong></li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1639, 'Medicine,', 'PM1523. Types Of Gastric Ulcers', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>This is the classification given in Harrisons 20th ed, Principles of Internal Medicine.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp; Type Of Ulcer</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Location</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Acid Production</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Surgical Management</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Type I</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Gastric body</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low</td>\n<td>Distal Gastrectomy Billroth Type 1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Type II</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Antrum</td>\n<td>&nbsp; &nbsp;Low to Normal</td>\n<td>Distal Gastrectomy and Vagotomy/PPI</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Type III</td>\n<td>Within 3cm of the pylorus; Accompanied by duodenal ulcers</td>\n<td>&nbsp; &nbsp;Normal or High</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Distal Gastrectomy and Vagotomy/PPI&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Type IV</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Cardia</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Low</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Pouchet, Csendes Procedure</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The other classification is Modified Johnsons Classification which is as follows:&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Modified Johnson classification</strong> for gastric ulcer</p>\n<p>I. Lesser curve, incisura - Normal Acid secretion</p>\n<p>II. Body of stomach, incisura + duodenal ulcer (active or healed) - Increased Acid secretion</p>\n<p>III. Prepyloric - Increased Acid secretion</p>\n<p>IV. High on lesser curve - Normal acid secretion</p>\n<p>V. Medication induced (NSAID/ acetylsalicylic acid), anywhere in stomach</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/bf5c4629d1994c429b07e815b3065147x1280x2177.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1640, 'Medicine', 'PM0774. ROME IV Diagnostic criteria for IBS', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p class=\bulletIndent1\>According to the Rome IV criteria, IBS is defined as recurrent <strong>abdominal pain </strong>for&nbsp;at least <strong>1 day per week</strong> in the last <strong>3 months</strong>. It must be associated with <strong>2 or more</strong> of the following criteria:</p>\n<ul>\n<li class=\bulletIndent2\>Related to defecation&nbsp;(improvement or worsening)</li>\n<li class=\bulletIndent2\>Associated with a change in stool frequency</li>\n<li class=\bulletIndent2\>Associated with a change in stool form (appearance)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The above criteria must be fulfilled for <strong>3 months</strong> with&nbsp;<strong>onset</strong>&nbsp;of some symptoms at least <strong>6 months</strong> before diagnosis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1641, 'Medicine', 'PM0419. Precipitating factors of Hepatic Encephalopathy', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Common precipitating factors of Hepatic Encephalopathy are</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Increased Nitrogen load:</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>GI bleeding</li>\n<li>Excess dietary protein</li>\n<li>Azotemia</li>\n<li>Constipation</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Drugs</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Narcotics</li>\n<li>Sedatives</li>\n<li>Excess diuretics</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Electrolytic imbalance</strong>:\n<ul>\n<li>Hypokalemia</li>\n<li>Alkalosis</li>\n<li>Hypoxia</li>\n<li>Hyponatremia</li>\n<li>Hypovolemia</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Miscellaneous</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Infection</li>\n<li>Surgery</li>\n<li>Superimposed liver disease</li>\n<li>Shunts</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1642, 'Medicine', 'PM2428. Autoantibodies Seen in Autoimmune Diseases', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\469\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Autoantibody</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Associated disease</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Antinuclear (ANA)</td>\n<td>\n<p>SLE (non-specific)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anticardiolipin, lupus anticoagulant</td>\n<td>SLE, APLA syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti-ds DNA, anti-Smith</td>\n<td>SLE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti-histone</td>\n<td>Drug-induced Lupus</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti-U1 RNP</td>\n<td>Mixed connective tissue disease</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Rheumatoid factor, anti-CCP</td>\n<td>Rheumatoid arthritis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti-Ro/SSA, Anti-La/SSB</td>\n<td>Sjögren’s syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti-Scl-70 (anti-DNA topoisomerase)</td>\n<td>Diffuse scleroderma</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anticentromere</td>\n<td>CREST syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Anti-SRP,&nbsp;Anti-Mi-2, Anti-Jo-1</td>\n<td>Polymyositis, Dermatomyositis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>p-ANCA/MPO</td>\n<td>Churg Strauss syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>c-ANCA</td>\n<td>Wegener (Granulomatosis with polyangiitis)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1643, 'Orthopaedics,', 'PM2038. The most commons of rheumatoid arthritis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Feature of RA</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Most common&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Involved joints</td>\n<td>MCP, Wrist, PIP(DIP spared)&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Spine involvement</td>\n<td>Cervical spine</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Extra-articular manifestation</td>\n<td>Subcutaneous nodules (mostly extensor surface)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cardiac manifestation</td>\n<td>Pericarditis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Valvular abnormality</td>\n<td>Mitral regurgitation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pulmonary manifestation</td>\n<td>Pleuritis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hematological manifestation</td>\n<td>Normochromic normocytic anemia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Neurological manifestation</td>\n<td>Compression neuropathies (mostly carpal tunnel syndrome)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Ocular manifestation</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Keratoconjunctivitis sicca</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lymphoma</td>\n<td>Diffuse large B-cell lymphoma</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cause of death</td>\n<td>Cardiovascular disease (coronary artery disease)</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1644, 'Medicine', 'PM1947. Diffuse Cutaneous Systemic Sclerosis  Versus Limited Cutaneous Systemic Sclerosis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\556\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Characteristic feature</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Diffuse cutaneous systemic sclerosis</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Limited cutaneous systemic sclerosis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Skin involvement</td>\n<td>\n<p>Rapid progression</p>\n<p>Involvement of the skin areas <strong>proximal</strong> <strong>to the knees or elbows</strong> or over the anterior chest, trunk, or abdomen</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Slow progression</p>\n<p>Limited to face and skin <strong>distal</strong> <strong>to the elbows and knees</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Raynaud’s phenomenon</td>\n<td>\n<p>Less severe</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Short history</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>More severe; commonly associated with critical limb ischemia.</p>\n<p><strong>Long history</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Musculoskeletal</td>\n<td><strong>Severe arthralgia</strong>, carpal tunnel syndrome, and tendon friction rubs</td>\n<td><strong>Mild</strong> arthralgia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pulmonary manifestation</td>\n<td>Interstitial lung disease more common</td>\n<td>Pulmonary artery hypertension (PAH) is equal in both</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Scleroderma renal crisis</td>\n<td>Occurs usually &lt;4 years of disease onset</td>\n<td>Very rare</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Calcinosis cutis</td>\n<td>Less common</td>\n<td>More common &amp;&nbsp;prominent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Auto-antibodies</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Anti-topoisomerase I</strong> (Scl-70)</p>\n<p>anti-RNA polymerase III</p>\n</td>\n<td><strong>Anti centromere</strong></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/35bb13425bb64e78b9164796e0c2fc29x1280x2412.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1645, 'Medicine,', 'PM1921. Joint Involvement in Various Arthritis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Joint Disorders</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Joints Commonly Involved</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Joints Com</strong><strong>monly </strong><strong>Spared</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>&nbsp;<strong>Osteoarthritis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Cervical and lumbosacral spine, PIP, DIP,&nbsp;1st CMC, hip, knee,&nbsp;1st MTP,&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>&nbsp;Elbow, Wrist, Ankle, MCP&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Rheumatoid Arthritis</strong></td>\n<td>Shoulder, Wrist, MCP, PIP, Knee, MTP&nbsp;</td>\n<td>DIP&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Ankylosing Spondylitis</strong></td>\n<td>Sacroiliac joint, intervertebral joints</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Psoriatic Arthritis</strong></td>\n<td>PIP,&nbsp;DIP</td>\n<td>Ray distribution*&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Ray distribution: Joint involvement tends to follow a pattern with all of the joints of one finger involved sparing the adjacent finger completely.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1646, 'Medicine', 'PM1844. Auto antibodies in a few disorders', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Auto-antibodies in <strong>myasthenia gravis</strong>:</p>\n<p>i)&nbsp;Anti-acetylcholine receptor (<strong>AChR</strong>) antibodies</p>\n<p>ii)&nbsp;Anti-muscle-specific kinase (<strong>MuSK</strong>) antibodies</p>\n<p>iii)&nbsp;Anti-low density lipoprotein receptor-related protein 4 (<strong>LRP4</strong>) antibodies</p>\n<p><strong>Anti-C1q antibodies</strong> are associated with <strong>systemic lupus erythematosus </strong>(SLE) and membrane proliferative glomerulonephritis (MPGN).&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Anti-Smith</strong> antibodies (Anti-Sm) are associated with SLE.</p>\n<p>Anti-lysosome associated membrane protein-2 <strong>(LAMP-2)</strong> antibodies are associated with certain types of vasculitis.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1647, 'Medicine', 'PM1563. Deformities in rheumatoid arthritis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Boutonnière deformity: </strong>Flexion of the PIP joint with hyperextension of the DIP joint.&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/f0250f1148284de1bd77c8d6e470c56fx720x960.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Swan-neck deformity</strong>: Hyperextension of the PIP joint with flexion of the DIP joint.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/560c6a73ecfc46e7aed6682bc24af2a4x720x1017.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Z line deformity: </strong>Radial deviation of the wrist with ulnar deviation of digits.&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/c60e1966a5314bbf8fd6c20a5ed7f625x800x600.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Eversion at hindfoot (subtalar joint), hallux valgus (shown below), hammertoe.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/798b7febef7a44699a664b1f1a5363cdx720x919.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Windswept deformities of toes - Valgus deformities of toes in one foot and varus in the other foot.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Piano-key movement </strong>of the ulnar styloid.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger finger</strong> due to flexor tendon synovitis.&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1648, 'Medicine,', 'PM1080. Difference between Gout and Pseudo-gout', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Finding</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Gout</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Pseudogout</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Crystal composition</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Monosodium urate</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Calcium pyrophosphate</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Shape</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Needle like</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Rhomboid</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Birefringence pattern</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Negative</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Weak positive</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Most commonly affected joint</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1<sup>st</sup> MTP</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Knee</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>X-ray findings</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Periarticular erosions with overhanging margins</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Chondrocalcinosis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1649, 'Medicine', 'PM0441. Churg Strauss', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>Eosinophilic Granulomatosis with polyangiitis (Churg Strauss Syndrome) is a <strong>necrotising granulomatous</strong> vasculitis. It involves <strong>small</strong> and medium-sized muscular arteries, capillaries, veins, and venules.</li>\n<li>It presents as a combination of <strong>asthma</strong>, peripheral and tissue <strong>eosinophilia</strong>,&nbsp;extravascular <strong>granulomas</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;vasculitis</strong> of multiple organ systems.</li>\n<li>The characteristic histopathological shows granulomatous reaction that can be present in the tissue or even within the walls of the vessels.</li>\n<li>&nbsp;Common organs affected in this condition are:\n<ul>\n<li>Lung- presents with severe asthmatic attacks and pulmonary infiltrates</li>\n<li>Mononueritis multiplex</li>\n<li>Skin lesions- presents as purpura and subcutaneous nodules</li>\n<li>Renal involvement</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Important laboratory findings seen are:\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Eosinophilia</strong> with levels of &gt; 1000 cells/µL</li>\n<li>Presence of <strong>pANCA</strong> antibodies</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Treatment- Glucocorticoids and mepolizumab (anti-IL-5 antibody) have been found to effective.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1650, 'Paediatrics,', 'PM0191. Kawasaki disease criteria', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Diagnostic criteria of Kawasaki disease</strong>:&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Fever of five days or more</strong> duration <strong>plus four</strong> <strong>out of the following</strong> five criteria:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Oropharyngeal changes (90% of cases)</li>\n<li>Changes in peripheral extremities (90% of cases)</li>\n<li>Cervical lymphadenopathy (~75% of cases)</li>\n<li>Polymorphous rash (95% of cases)</li>\n<li>Bilateral non-purulent conjunctival injection (90% of cases)</li>\n</ol></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1651, 'Medicine', 'PM2453. Treatment of Asthma based on severity of symptoms (GINA-2022)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Asthma management - GINA 2022</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/3349e17dd3a64530b8cda3c9732af613x1280x3702.792665726375.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->');
INSERT INTO db_pearl_m (pid, subject, pearl_title, pearl_desc) VALUES
(1652, 'Medicine', 'PM2392. Clinical prediction for pulmonary embolism: Well’s, Modified Well’s and Pulmonary Embolism Rule out Criteria (PERC)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Signs/symptoms</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Score</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Clinical signs of DVT</td>\n<td>3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diagnosis other than pulmonary embolism is less likely</td>\n<td>3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Heart rate &gt;100 bpm</td>\n<td>1.5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Immobilization for &gt;3 days or surgery in the last 4 weeks</td>\n<td>1.5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Past history of DVT/pulmonary embolism</td>\n<td>1.5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Hemoptysis</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Malignancy</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Three-level score probability:</strong></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Wells criteria</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Score</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Low</td>\n<td>&lt;2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Moderate</td>\n<td>2-6</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High</td>\n<td>&gt;6</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><strong>Two-level score probability:</strong></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Modified Wells criteria</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Score</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pulmonary embolism unlikely</td>\n<td>≤4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pulmonary embolism likely</td>\n<td>&gt;4&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Pulmonary embolism rule out criteria (PERC):</strong></p>\n<p>This is a quick OPD/casualty tool to rule out pulmonary embolism in patients with low clinical probability. It comprises <strong>eight clinical variables</strong>. If the patient meets all eight criteria, there is no need for further investigations. The variables include:&nbsp;</p>\n<ol>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Age &lt;50 years</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Heart rate &lt;100 bpm</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>SpO2 ≥95%</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>No unilateral leg swelling</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>No hemoptysis</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>No recent trauma or surgery</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>No history of venous thromboembolism</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>No use of hormonal therapy.</li>\n</ol></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1653, 'Medicine', 'PM1879. Types of pleural effusion', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Transudative Pleural effusion</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Congestive heart failure (most common)</li>\n<li>Cirrhosis</li>\n<li>Nephrotic syndrome</li>\n<li>Myxedema&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Peritoneal dialysis</li>\n<li>Urinothorax</li>\n<li>Hypoalbuminemia</li>\n<li>Constrictive pericarditis</li>\n<li>Superior vena cava obstruction</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Exudative Pleural effusion&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Infections:&nbsp;Tuberculosis, pneumonia,&nbsp;intraabdominal abscess (like- liver abscess)</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Malignancy:&nbsp;Pleural mesothelioma,&nbsp;metastasis,&nbsp;lymphoma</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Connective tissue diseases:&nbsp;SLE,&nbsp;rheumatoid arthritis</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Drugs:&nbsp;Amiodarone,&nbsp;bromocriptine,&nbsp;dantrolene,&nbsp;dasatinib,&nbsp;methysergide,&nbsp;nitrofurantoin</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Others:\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Pancreatitis</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Asbestosis</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Pulmonary embolism</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Hemothorax</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Chylothorax</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Meigs syndrome&nbsp;</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Dressler syndrome (post-myocardial infarction or cardiac surgery)</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Yellow nail syndrome&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1654, 'Medicine', 'PM1863. Types of Respiratory Failure', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Type</td>\n<td>Name</td>\n<td>Mechanism</td>\n<td>Associated conditions</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>I</td>\n<td>Acute <strong>hypoxemic</strong> respiratory failure</td>\n<td>\n<p>Alveolar flooding and subsequent intrapulmonary shunt physiology.</p>\n<p>Low pO2</p>\n<p>Normal/ low pCO2</p>\n<p>High (pAO2-paO2)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Sepsis</p>\n<p>Gastric aspiration</p>\n<p>Pneumonia</p>\n<p>Near-drowning</p>\n<p>Multiple blood transfusions</p>\n<p>Pancreatitis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>II</td>\n<td>\n<p>Hypoxemia with <strong>hypercapnia</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Results from the inability to eliminate carbon dioxide effectively.</p>\n<p>Low pO2</p>\n<p>High pCO2</p>\n<p>Normal (pAO2-paO2)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Drug overdose</p>\n<p>Brainstem injury</p>\n<p>Sleep-disordered breathing</p>\n<p>Severe hypothyroidism</p>\n<p>Myasthenia gravis</p>\n<p>Guillain-Barre syndrome</p>\n<p>Amyotrophic lateral sclerosis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>III</td>\n<td>Peri-operative respiratory failure</td>\n<td>Results from lung atelectasis.</td>\n<td>After general anesthesia.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>IV</td>\n<td>Shock</td>\n<td>Results from hypoperfusion of respiratory muscles in patients with shock</td>\n<td>Cardiogenic shock.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>pO2- partial pressure of oxygen</p>\n<p>pCO2- partial pressure of carbon dioxide</p>\n<p>(pAO2-paO2)- alveolar- arterial oxygen gradient</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1655, 'Medicine', 'PM1845. Incidence of lung cancer according to histology', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/db74b9a5468642d5806deed4dfad448cx1280x1541.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1656, 'Medicine', 'PM1843. Lobes involved in various lung diseases', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Mnemonic to easily remember the lobe of lung involved in CTD is:</p>\n<p>Upper Lobe - <strong>CHARTS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>C</strong>oal workers pneumoconiosis (CWP), silicosis, berylliosis</li>\n<li><strong>H</strong>istiocytosis X (LCH)</li>\n<li><strong>A</strong>nkylosing spondylitis, ABPA</li>\n<li><strong>R</strong>adiation</li>\n<li><strong>T</strong>uberculosis</li>\n<li><strong>S</strong>arcoidosis</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Lower lobes - <strong>RAIDS</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>R</strong>heumatoid arthritis</li>\n<li><strong>A</strong>sbestosis</li>\n<li><strong>I</strong>diopathic pulmonary fibrosis (IPF) and non-specific interstitial pneumonia (NSIP)</li>\n<li><strong>D</strong>rugs: bleomycin, busulfan, amiodarone, methotrexate, nitrofurantoin</li>\n<li><strong>S</strong>cleroderma</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1657, 'Medicine', 'PM1840. Extrinsic vs Intrinsic asthma', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Component</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Extrinsic asthma</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Intrinsic asthma</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Other names</td>\n<td>Atopic/ allergic asthma</td>\n<td>Non-atopic/ non-allergic/ idiosyncratic asthma</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Associated with&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Atopy, drug or food allergy (past or family history)</td>\n<td>Samter’s triad (asthma + aspirin sensitivity + sinus disease with recurrent nasal polyps)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Onset</td>\n<td>Childhood</td>\n<td>Adult</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Inflammation</td>\n<td>Eosinophil mediated</td>\n<td>Neutrophil mediated</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>IgE levels</td>\n<td>↑ IgE (type 1 hypersensitivity)</td>\n<td>Normal IgE (negative skin prick test)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Most common trigger</td>\n<td>Dermatophagoides (House mite)</td>\n<td>\n<p>Superantigen -&nbsp;<br><em>S. aureus</em> enterotoxin</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Response to inhaled corticosteroids</td>\n<td>Responds well&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Decreased short term response</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Prognosis</td>\n<td>Good</td>\n<td>Bad</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1658, 'Medicine', 'PM1821. Evaluation of solitary pulmonary nodule', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Nodule size (a):</td>\n<td>Low-risk patient (b):</td>\n<td>High-risk patient (c):</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>≤4 mm</td>\n<td>No follow-up needed (d)</td>\n<td>Follow-up at 12 months; if unchanged, no further follow-up</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&gt;4–6 mm</td>\n<td>Follow-up CT at 12 months; if unchanged, no further follow-up</td>\n<td>Follow-up CT at 6–12 months; then 18–24 months if no change</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&gt;6–8 mm</td>\n<td>Follow-up CT at 6–12 months; then 18–24 months if no change</td>\n<td>Follow-up CT at 3–6 months; then 9–12 and 24 months if no change</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&gt;8 mm</td>\n<td>Follow-up CT at 3, 9, and 24 months; dynamic contrast enhanced CT, PET, and/or biopsy</td>\n<td>Same as low-risk patient</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>(a) Average of largest and smallest axial diameters of the nodule</p>\n<p>(b) No smoking history and absence of other risk factors</p>\n<p>(c) Previous or current smoking history or other risk factors</p>\n<p>(d) Risk of malignancy (&lt;0.1%) is substantially lower than for an asymptomatic smoker</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1659, 'Medicine', 'PM1172. PFT for obstructive vs restrictive diseases', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p><strong>PFT</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p><strong>Obstructive disease</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p><strong>Restrictive disease</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>FVC</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Decreased</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Decreased (&lt;80% predicted)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>FEV1</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Decreased (&lt;80% predicted)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>Decreased</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>FEV1% (FEV1/FVC)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Decreased (&lt;0.7)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Normal/ increased (&gt;0.7)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>FEF 25-75</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>&lt;50% predicted</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Normal/ decreased</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>TLC</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Normal/ increased</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Decreased</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>RV</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Increased</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>Decreased</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\150\>\n<p>DLCO</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<ul>\n<li>Normal or increased in asthma</li>\n<li>Decreased in emphysema</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td width=\150\>\n<ul>\n<li>Decreased in intrinsic restrictive disease</li>\n<li>Normal in neuromuscular or musculoskeletal restrictive disease</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>FVC: Forced Vital Capacity</p>\n<p>FEV1: Forced expiratory volume in 1 second</p>\n<p>FEF 25-75: Forced expiratory flow at 25-75% vital capacity</p>\n<p>TLC: Total lung capacity</p>\n<p>RV: Residual volume</p>\n<p>DLCO: Diffusion capacity of lung for Carbon monoxide.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1660, 'Medicine', 'PM1171. CURB-65 Criteria', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>This is a score to determine the severity of pneumonia.</p>\n<p>The CURB-65 criteria include five variables(1 point for each variable):</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>C</strong>onfusion&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Blood <strong>U</strong>rea Nitrogen (BUN) &gt;7&nbsp;<span class=\nowrap\>mmol/L</span></li>\n<li><strong>R</strong>espiratory rate ≥30/min&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>B</strong>lood pressure, systolic ≤90 mmHg or diastolic ≤60 mmHg&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Age ≥<strong>65</strong> years.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Management:</p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>0 point: Treat as an outpatient</span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>1 to 2 points: Admitted to the hospital</span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>≥3 points: ICU admission</span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\><strong>Treatment of Community-Acquired Pneumonia</strong>&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>Score - 0: The drug of choice is macrolides. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Azithromycin 500mg OD </span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; or </span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Clarithromycin&nbsp; 500mg BD </span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; or </span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Doxycycline&nbsp; 100mg BD.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>Score - 1: Treated with azithromycin&nbsp; 500mg OD + ceftriaxone 2gm OD.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Respiratory quinolones (Levofloxacin) are not preferred. </span></p>\n<p><span class=\medCalcFontOneBold\>Score - &gt;2: Azithromycin 500mg OD + Ceftriaxone 2gm IV OD and specific management.<br></span></p>\n<p>NOTE:- In a<strong> modified </strong>version of the CURB-65, the criteria of blood urea nitrogen has been removed.</p>\n<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;This elimination removes the need for lab testing.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1661, 'Medicine', 'PM1165. Types of Bronchiectasis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Cylindrical/Tubular</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Saccular/Varicose</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Cystic</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Mildest form of&nbsp;bronchiectasis</li>\n<li>Loss of&nbsp;normal airway tapering</li>\n<li>Bronchi have a uniform calibre, have parallel walls&nbsp;tram track sign and signet&nbsp;ring sign</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Further distortion of the&nbsp;airway wall along with&nbsp;more mucous and sputum&nbsp;production</li>\n<li>Beaded bronchi with interspersed sites of&nbsp;relative narrowing</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Most severe form of&nbsp;bronchiectasis and least common</li>\n<li>This form has large air spaces&nbsp;and a honeycombed&nbsp;appearance</li>\n<li>Air fluid levels present</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/11950d44a96e48f785aa4b59a074c06cx284x115.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1662, 'Medicine', 'PM0581. Causes of predominantly unilateral pleural effusion', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Predominantly right-</strong><strong>sided pleural </strong><strong>effusion</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Predominantly </strong><strong>left-sided pleural </strong><strong>effusion</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Cirrhosis of the liver</p>\n<p>(hepatic hydrothorax)</p>\n</td>\n<td>Acute pancreatitis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Amebic liver abscess</p>\n</td>\n<td>Aortic dissection</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;Meig’s syndrome</td>\n<td>Esophageal rupture</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Cardiac failure</p>\n<p>( B/L&gt;&gt;right-sided)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Dressler’s syndrome</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1663, 'Medicine', 'PM0009. Named lung diseases', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Bagassosis</p>\n</td>\n<td>Pneumoconiosis due to sugarcane</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Byssinosis (brown lung disease/ Monday fever)</td>\n<td>Pneumoconiosis due to cotton fiber</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Farmer’s lung</td>\n<td>Pneumoconiosis due to Thermophilic actinomycetes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bird Fancier’s lung</td>\n<td>Hypersensitivity pneumonitis caused by bird droppings</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Chalicosis (flint disease)&nbsp;</td>\n<td>In stonecutters, due to inhalation of fine particles of stone</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Caplan’s syndrome</td>\n<td>&nbsp;RA + pneumoconiosis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lofgrens syndrome</td>\n<td>An acute presentation of sarcoidosis, consisting of arthritis, erythema nodosum, and bilateral hilar adenopathy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Bornholm’s disease (epidemic pleurodynia)</td>\n<td>associated with Coxsackie B virus</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1664, 'Medicine', 'PM2427. Hemodialysis vs Peritoneal dialysis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Difference between Hemodialysis and Peritoneal dialysis</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Hemodialysis</td>\n<td>Peritoneal dialysis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Comparatively difficult access</td>\n<td>Easy access</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Better clearance</td>\n<td>Good clearance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Short time for treatment</td>\n<td>Longer time may be required</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Principle:<br><br>Solute removal through a semi-permeable membrane.</td>\n<td>\n<p>Principle:</p>\n<p>Solute removal through a peritoneal membrane</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Must be done in hospital</td>\n<td>Can be done at home</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Complications:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Hypotension</li>\n<li>Disequilibrium syndrome</li>\n<li>Muscle cramps</li>\n<li>Anaphylaxis reaction</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Complications :</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Peritonitis</li>\n<li>Catheter-associated non-peritoneal infections</li>\n<li>Weight gain</li>\n<li>Metabolic disturbances</li>\n<li>Residual uremia</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1665, 'Medicine', 'PM2381. Renal Tubular Syndromes', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/7e5e18bdaa4a442981637c52affb466fx1280x3492.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1666, 'Medicine', 'PM2212. Risk Factors of UTI', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Risk Factors for Urinary Tract Infection</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Demographic factors</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Female Gender</li>\n<li>Male infants (UTI is Males&gt;females during infancy alone)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Structural</strong> factors - Any anatomical hindrance to drainage</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Vesicoureteral reflux (for pyelonephritis)</li>\n<li>Neuropathic Bladder</li>\n<li>Pregnancy</li>\n<li>Constipation</li>\n<li>Obstructive uropathy</li>\n<li>Uncircumcised male</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Practices &amp; Procedures</strong>:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Toilet training</li>\n<li>Voiding dysfunction</li>\n<li>Wiping from back to front in Females (not males)</li>\n<li>Tight clothing (underwear)</li>\n<li>Urethral instrumentation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Infective Factors</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Pinworm infestation</li>\n<li>Infection of Bacteria with P fimbriae</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1667, 'Medicine', 'PM2110. Characteristics of renal tubular acidosis (RTA)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td rowspan=\2\>&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>\n<td colspan=\2\>Hypokalemic RTA&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Hyperkalemic RTA</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Type 1 RTA</p>\n</td>\n<td>Type 2 RTA&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Type 4 RTA</p>\n<p>Most Common</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Primary</p>\n<p>defect</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Impaired distal acidification</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Reduced proximal</p>\n<p>HCO<sub>3</sub>&nbsp;resorption</p>\n</td>\n<td>Decreased aldosterone secretion or aldosterone resistance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Plasma HCO3</p>\n<p>(mEq/L)</p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;<span class=\symbol\>&lt;</span>15</td>\n<td>12 to 20</td>\n<td>&gt;17</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Plasma potassium</td>\n<td>\n<p>&nbsp; Low</p>\n<p>(normalizes with alkalinization)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>&nbsp;Low</p>\n<p>(Decreased further by alkalinization)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>High</strong></p>\n<p>(correcting the hyperkalemia alone will improve the acidosis by increasing ammonium availability)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Urine pH</td>\n<td>&gt;5.5</td>\n<td>\n<p>&gt; 5.3 if the serum HCO<sub>3&nbsp;</sub>exceeds the tubules&nbsp;HCO<sub>3&nbsp;</sub></p>\n<p>reabsorptive threshold.</p>\n<p><strong>&lt; 5.3</strong> when the serum HCO<sub>3</sub>&nbsp;is reduced to levels that can be largely reabsorbed despite defective proximal tubule reabsorptive mechanisms.</p>\n</td>\n<td>&lt;5.5</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Urine</p>\n<p>anion gap</p>\n</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n<td>Negative</td>\n<td>Positive</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Nephrolithiasis/ Nephrocalcinosis</p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Yes</td>\n<td>&nbsp;No</td>\n<td>&nbsp;No</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1668, 'Medicine', 'PM1891. Most Commons in Glomerulopathies', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\>Most common cause of:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Primary glomerulonephritis in the world</td>\n<td>IgA nephropathy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Secondary glomerulonephritis in the&nbsp;world</td>\n<td>Diabetic nephropathy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nephrotic syndrome&nbsp;in adults</td>\n<td>Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis &gt; membranous nephropathy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Nephrotic syndrome&nbsp;in&nbsp;children</td>\n<td>Minimal change disease</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Glomerulopathy in colon cancer or lung cancer</td>\n<td>Membranous nephropathy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Renal pathology in leprosy</td>\n<td>Membranoproliferative glomerulonephritis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Renal pathology in syphillis</td>\n<td>Membranous nephropathy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Renal pathology in hepatitis C</td>\n<td>Cryoglobulinemic glomerulonephritis</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Renal pathology in hepatitis B</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Membranous nephropathy</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1669, 'Medicine', 'PM1885. Urinary Casts and Their Significance', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/8ce4f74ab9824f42b8cb05ac3433314cx1280x3456.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1670, 'Medicine', 'PM1877. Color of urine  in different conditions', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Normal color of urine is <strong>pale straw</strong> due to presence of <strong>urochrome.</strong></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Abnormality</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Cause</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Smokey or cloudy</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>AGN</li>\n<li>Nephrotic syndrome</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gross blood</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Urological causes&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Nephro causes</li>\n<li>Hematological causes, e.g. PNH</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Red without blood [brownish tinge]</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Rhabdomyolysis&nbsp; &nbsp;</li>\n<li>Beetroot ingestion&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tea- or cola-colored urine</td>\n<td>Hemoglobinuria</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>High-colored urine</td>\n<td>Bilirubinuria</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Darkens on standing</td>\n<td>Alkaptonuria</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;Due to Drugs:&nbsp;</p>\n<table width=\251\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Abnormality&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Drugs&nbsp;</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Orange</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Rifamycins (rifampicin, rifabutin, rifapentine)</li>\n<li>B-complex&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Blue</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Amitriptyline</li>\n<li>Methylene blue</li>\n<li>Copper poisoning</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Brown</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Chloroquine</li>\n<li>Quinine</li>\n<li>Primaquine</li>\n<li>Nitrofurantoin&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Yellow</td>\n<td>Tetracycline&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pinkish</td>\n<td>Deferoxamine</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Green</td>\n<td>Triamterene</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Darkens on standing</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Metronidazole</li>\n<li>Methyldopa</li>\n<li>Imipenem-cilastin</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1671, 'Medicine', 'PM2441. Supraventricular tachycardias', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Supraventricular tachycardias with narrow QRS complex:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Narrow QRS with regular RR interval</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;Tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;ECG features</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sinus tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td>Normal P wave, normal ECG features except for the rate</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Focal atrial tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td>A single type of abnormal p wave morphology is seen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Junctional tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td>No p waves. Heart rate is 100- 200/ min</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>AV nodal reentry tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td>No p waves. Pseudo R waves may be seen. Heart rate is 150-250/ min</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Atrioventricular reentry tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td>P wave always follows QRS. RP interval&lt; PR interval</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Atrial flutter</strong></td>\n<td>Sawtooth shaped flutter waves are seen</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Narrow QRS with irregular RR interval</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>Tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;ECG features</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Atrial fibrillation</strong></td>\n<td>No distinct p waves seen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Multifocal atrial tachycardia</strong></td>\n<td>More than 3 different abnormal p wave morphologies are seen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Atrial flutter/tachycardia with variable block</strong></td>\n<td>ECG features of heart block are seen.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Supraventricular tachycardias with wide QRS complex:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Antidromic AVRT (atrioventricular reentry tachycardia)</li>\n<li>Supraventricular tachycardias with bundle branch block</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1672, 'Medicine', 'PM2440. ECG patterns of various ventricular arrhythmias', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Ventricular tachycardia</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/097b95729fa14ac68da475ce6288a968x1088x570.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Polymorphic ventricular tachycardia associated with QTc prolongation- Torsades de pointes</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/a8ebe0b5757c4efca4f5dd15c6d24e99x1268x324.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Ventricular flutter</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/666962cd0f424000b7e84123f719f120x502x282.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Ventricular fibrillation</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/25067efa869941baa6a40b54599b371ax1049x213.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1673, 'Medicine', 'PM2439. Wolff Parkinson White Syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Wolff Parkinson White Syndrome</strong>&nbsp;(WPW) is characterized by an abnormal accessory pathway in the heart leading to arrhythmias.</p>\n<p><strong>Pathology</strong>- Born with an accessory pathway, the bundle of Kent which connects the atria and ventricle. The electrical impulses from the SA node reach the ventricles earlier via the accessory pathway as there is no AV nodal delay in this pathway. This leads to the preexcitation of the ventricle and initiation of ventricular contraction. This ventricular contraction is prolonged when the impulse via the AV nodal pathway reaches the ventricles.</p>\n<p><strong>Most common location</strong> of the accessory pathway-&nbsp;between the left atrium and free wall of the left ventricle</p>\n<p><strong>ECG changes</strong>:</p>\n<p><strong>Shortened PR interval</strong>- because of the early initiation of ventricular depolarization</p>\n<p><strong>Prolonged QRS duration</strong>- because of the AV nodal impulse reaching the ventricles after the aberrant impulse.</p>\n<p><strong>Delta waves</strong>- slurred upstroke of QRS complex</p>\n<p>The given ECG shows delta waves marked with red arrows:</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/b00a7f28fc9540629f591281df010cf4x791x183.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Treatment:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Catheter ablation</strong>&nbsp;is the treatment of choice.</li>\n<li>Anti-arrhythmic drugs like procainamide, amiodarone, quinidine, propafenone, dofetilide are used in slowing conduction in the accessory pathway (prolong refractory period).</li>\n<li>IV procainamide is the drug of choice in a hemodynamically stable WPW presenting with atrial fibrillation.</li>\n<li>DC cardioversion is done in&nbsp;hemodynamically unstable patients.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1674, 'Surgery,', 'PM2291. Risk Factors for Venous Thromboembolism', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The risk factors for venous thromboembolism (pulmonary embolism and DVT) are as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Major trauma</strong> like spinal cord injury or fracture of lower limb</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Surgery</strong> like hip or knee replacement</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Hospitalization</strong> for heart failure or atrial fibrillation/flutter within last 3 months</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Myocardial infarction</strong>&nbsp;within last 3 months</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\><strong>Previous venous thromboembolism</strong></li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Infections and inflammatory bowel disease</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Autoimmune diseases:\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Antiphospholipid antibody (APLA)</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>SLE</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Inherited thrombophilias:\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Factor V leiden mutation</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Deficiency of antithrombin III</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Deficiency of protein C or protein S</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Hypercoagulable states:\n<ul>\n<li>Pregnancy and postpartum period</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>COPD</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Nephrotic syndrome</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Polycythemia vera</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Malignancies</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Iatrogenic:\n<ul>\n<li aria-level=\1\>OCPs</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Hormone replacement therapy</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Chemotherapeutic drugs</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Insertion of central venous lines</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Varicose veins</li>\n<li aria-level=\1\>Prolonged car or air travel.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1675, 'Medicine,', 'PM2066. Revised Jones criteria for diagnosis of Acute Rheumatic Fever (ARF)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Revised Jones criteria for the diagnosis of rheumatic fever are as follows:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\>Major criteria</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Low-risk populations*</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Moderate- and high-risk populations*</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Carditis- Clinical or subclinical</td>\n<td>Carditis- Clinical or subclinical</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Arthritis- <strong>Polyarthritis only</strong></td>\n<td>Arthritis- <strong>P</strong><strong>olyarthritis/polyarthralgia/monoarthritis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Chorea</td>\n<td>Chorea</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Erythema marginatum</td>\n<td>Erythema marginatum</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Subcutaneous nodules</td>\n<td>Subcutaneous nodules</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\>Minor criteria&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Polyarthralgia</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Monoarthralgia</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fever&nbsp;(≥38.5°C)</td>\n<td>Fever (≥38°C)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>ESR ≥60 mm in the first hour and/or CRP ≥3.0 mg/dL</td>\n<td>ESR ≥30 mm/hr and/or CRP ≥3.0 mg/dL</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Prolonged PR interval</strong>, after accounting for age variability (unless carditis is a major criterion)</td>\n<td>Prolonged PR interval, after accounting for age variability (unless carditis is a major criterion)&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\>For all patient populations with evidence of preceding Group A Streptococcal infection:(Increased ASLO/ anti-DNAse B titer or positive throat culture for group A streptococcus or positive rapid streptococcal carbohydrate antigen test)&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diagnosis of initial ARF</td>\n<td>2 Major criteria or 1 major plus 2 minor criteria</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Diagnosis of recurrent ARF</td>\n<td>2 Major or 1 major and 2 minor or 3 minor criteria</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>*Low-risk populations are those with ARF incidence ≤2 per 100 000 school-aged children or all-age rheumatic heart disease prevalence of ≤1 per 1000 population per year. If the incidence exceeds the given limit, then it is moderate-high risk populations.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1676, 'Medicine', 'PM1846. The causes of holosystolic murmur are:', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp; 1. Mitral regurgitation</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Best heard at the apex</li>\n<li>Radiates to axilla or base</li>\n<li>Decreases in intensity with amyl nitrate</li>\n<li>A2 is not heard at the apex</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp; 2. Tricuspid regurgitation</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Best heard at lower left sternal border</li>\n<li>Radiates to the epigastrium and right sternal border</li>\n<li>Increases in intensity during inspiration</li>\n<li>Prominent c-v waves seen in JVP</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp; 3. Ventricular septal defect</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Beat heard over left 3<sup>rd</sup> and 4<sup>th</sup> intercostal space</li>\n<li>Radiates widely</li>\n<li>Palpable thrill present</li>\n<li>Decreases in intensity with amyl nitrate</li>\n<li>Wide splitting of S2 seen</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1677, 'Medicine', 'PM1834. Cardiac conditions requiring antibiotic prophylaxis for infective endocarditis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>High risk cardiac conditions for development of Infective endocarditis and require antibiotic prophylaxis are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Prosthetic valves</li>\n<li>History of infective endocarditis</li>\n<li>Few congenital heart diseases which include:<br>\n<ul>\n<li>Unrepaired cyanotic CHD, including palliative shunts and conduit</li>\n<li>Completely repaired congenital heart defect with prosthetic material or device, whether placed by surgery or by catheter intervention, during the first 6 months after the procedure</li>\n<li>Repaired CHD with residual defects at the site or adjacent to the site of a prosthetic patch or prosthetic device</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Cardiac transplantation recipients with cardiac valvular disease</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1678, 'Medicine', 'PM1738. Revised 2017 ACC guidelines on Hypertension:', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Systolic BP (mm Hg)</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Diastolic BP</strong> <strong>(mm Hg)</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Management</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Normal</strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;&lt; 120</td>\n<td>&lt; 80</td>\n<td>Lifestyle modification</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Elevated BP</strong></td>\n<td>120 -129</td>\n<td>&lt; 80</td>\n<td>Lifestyle modification</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Stage 1 HT</strong></td>\n<td>130 -139 (or)</td>\n<td>80 -89</td>\n<td>\n<p>Lifestyle modification(Antihypertensive medication only if</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Previous stroke / CAD / Heart attack</li>\n<li>Diabetic</li>\n<li>CKD</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Stage 2 HT</strong></td>\n<td>&gt; 140 (or)</td>\n<td>&nbsp;&gt; 90</td>\n<td>Anti-hypertensive medication + Lifestyle modification</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Hypertensive crisis</strong></td>\n<td>&gt; 180 (or)</td>\n<td>&gt;120</td>\n<td>Patients needing prompt changes in medication if there are no other indications of problems, or immediate hospitalization if there are signs of organ damage.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1679, 'Medicine', 'PM1679. CHADS2 VASc Score (Risk of stroke in AF)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>RISK FACTOR</strong></td>\n<td><strong>POINTS</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>C</strong>- Congestive Heart Failure</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>H</strong>- Hypertension</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>A<sub>2</sub></strong><sub>-&nbsp;</sub>Age &gt;= 75 years</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>D</strong>- Diabetes</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>S<sub>2</sub></strong>- Prior stroke or TIA</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>V</strong>-&nbsp;Vascular disease&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>A</strong>-&nbsp;Age 65–74 years</td>\n<td>&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>S<sub>c</sub></strong>- Sex category (Female sex)</td>\n<td>&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table width=\376\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>CHA<sub>2</sub>DS<sub>2</sub>-VASc Score</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Stroke rate per 100 Patient Years</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>1.3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>2.2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3.2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>4.0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>6.7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>9.8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>\n<p>9.6</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8</td>\n<td>6.7</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9</td>\n<td>15.2</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1680, 'Medicine,', 'PM1655. Prophylaxis for DVT', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\><strong>Mechanical prophylaxis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Early ambulation</td>\n<td>\n<p>Acts by activating the calf pump mechanism</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pneumatic compression stocking</td>\n<td>\n<p>Prevents stasis by periodically compressing the calves</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\><strong>Pharmacological prophylaxis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Low molecular weight heparin (LMWH) - Enoxaparin</p>\n<p>Fondaparinux</p>\n</td>\n<td>Prevent thrombus formation by inhibiting factor Xa</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Apixaban</p>\n<p>Rivaroxaban&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Oral factor Xa inhibitors</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Unfractionated heparin (UFH)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Prevents action of factors VIII - XII and production of thrombin/fibrin.</p>\n<p>Used in renal insufficiency</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Warfarin</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Inhibits hepatic production of factors II, VII, IX and X</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1681, 'Medicine', 'PM1227. Management of Hypertensive Emergency', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/9addcf0641a14be88a24f231435de7ebx883x489.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1682, 'Medicine', 'PM1226. Target BP in hypertensive patients- European Society of Cardiology guidelines 2018', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\672\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Age group</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Hypertension</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Coexisting diabetes</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Coexisting chronic kidney disease</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Coexisting coronary artery disease</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Coexisting stroke/ TIA</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>18-65 years</p>\n<p>(Target systolic range- if tolerated)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>120-130 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>120-130 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>130-140 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>120-130 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>120-130 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>65-79 years</p>\n<p>(Target systolic range- if tolerated)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>130-139 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>130-139 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>130-139 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>130-139 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>130-139 mmHg</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Office diastolic measurement</td>\n<td>70-79mmHg</td>\n<td>70-79mmHg</td>\n<td>70-79mmHg</td>\n<td>&nbsp;70-79mmHg</td>\n<td>&nbsp;70-79mmHg</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->');
INSERT INTO db_pearl_m (pid, subject, pearl_title, pearl_desc) VALUES
(1683, 'Medicine', 'PM1223. European society of cardiology guidelines for treatment of hypertension', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\489\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p><strong>Indication</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\339\>\n<p><strong>Initial treatment of choice&nbsp;</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Hypertension alone or hypertension with diabetes/ cerebrovascular disease</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\339\>\n<p>ACEi/ARB + CCB/diuretic (A+C or A+D)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Hypertension with coronary artery disease</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\339\>\n<p>ACEi/ ARB + beta blocker/CCB (A+B or A+C)</p>\n<p>or</p>\n<p>beta-blocker + diuretic (B+D)</p>\n<p>or&nbsp;</p>\n<p>CCB+ diuretic/ beta-blocker (C+B or C+D)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Hypertension with chronic kidney disease</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\339\>\n<p>ACEi/ARB + CCB/diuretic (A+C or A+D)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Hypertension with heart failure and reduced ejection fraction</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\339\>\n<p>ACEI/ ARB + diuretic + beta-blocker (A+D+B)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Pregnancy</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\339\>\n<p>Labetalol, Nifedipine, methyldopa</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>ACEi – Angiotensin-converting enzyme inhibitors</p>\n<p>ARB – Angiotensin II receptor blockers</p>\n<p>CCB – Calcium Channel Blockers</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1684, 'Medicine', 'PM1222. American Heart Association (AHA) 2019 guidelines for hypertension management', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>According to the AHA hypertension guidelines, 2019, pharmacologic treatment for hypertension is recommended</p>\n<ul>\n<li>In patients who&nbsp;have <strong>≥10% estimated 10year ASCVD risk,&nbsp;</strong>when&nbsp;<strong>BP ≥ 130/80 mmHg</strong>&nbsp;</li>\n<li>In patients who have <strong>&lt;10%&nbsp;estimated 10year ASCVD risk&nbsp;</strong>when<strong>&nbsp;</strong><strong>BP ≥ 140/90</strong> <strong>mmHg</strong>&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;ASCVD - Atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease</p>\n<p>ASCVD risk is calculated using a calculator provided by the American Heart Association.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Lifestyle modifications in the management of hypertension</strong></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Intervention</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Goal</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Impact on BP</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1. Weight reduction</td>\n<td>The best goal is ideal body weight</td>\n<td>-5 mmHg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2. Dietary sodium restriction</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Total sodium - &lt;1.5g/day (AHA 2019 guidelines)</li>\n<li>Total NaCl (salt) intake - &lt;6g/day</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>-5/6 mmHg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3. Enhanced potassium intake</td>\n<td>3.5 - 5g/day</td>\n<td>-4/5 mmHg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4. DASH dietary pattern&nbsp;</td>\n<td>high in vegetables, fruits, low-fat dairy products, whole grains, poultry, fish, and nuts and low in sweets, sugar-sweetened beverages, red meats, and saturated and total fat.</td>\n<td>-11 mmHg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5. Physical activity</td>\n<td>Aerobic exercise, dynamic resistance and isometric resistance</td>\n<td>-4-8 mmHg</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6. Moderation in alcohol consumption</td>\n<td><span class=\Y0NH2b CLPzrc\>In individuals who drink alcohol - ≤</span> 2 drinks/ day for men and <span class=\Y0NH2b CLPzrc\>≤</span> 1 drink/ day for women</td>\n<td><span class=\Y0NH2b CLPzrc\>-4 mmHg</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>DASH – Dietary Approaches to Stop Hypertension</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Target BP in hypertensives:</strong></p>\n<table width=\658\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Clinical condition</strong></td>\n<td><strong>BP Goal, mm Hg</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Clinical CVD or&nbsp;10 year ASCVD risk&nbsp; &gt; 10%</td>\n<td>&lt;130/80</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>No clinical CVD and 10 year ASCVD risk &lt; 10%</td>\n<td>&lt;130/80</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adults with CKD</td>\n<td>&lt;130/80</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Adults with Type 2 DM&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&lt;130/80</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1685, 'Medicine', 'PM1221. Causes of Secondary Hypertension', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Renal parenchymal</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>Glomerulonephritis, renal cysts, renal tumors</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Renovascular</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>Renal artery stenosis,<strong>&nbsp;</strong>arteriosclerotic, fibromuscular dysplasia</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Adrenal</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>Primary aldosteronism, Cushing’s syndrome, pheochromocytoma</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Aortic coarctation</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Obstructive sleep apnea</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Pre-eclampsia/ eclampsia</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Neurogenic</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>Psychogenic, polyneuritis (acute porphyria, lead poisoning), acute increased ICP, acute spinal cord section</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Endocrine</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>Hypothyroidism, hyperthyroidism, hypercalcemia, acromegaly</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Medications</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>High-dose estrogens, adrenal steroids, appetite suppressants, cyclosporine, tricyclic antidepressants, MAO inhibitors, NSAIDS</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\149\>\n<p>Mendelian forms</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\329\>\n<p>Liddle’s syndrome, Gordon’s syndrome, MEN 2A &amp; 2B</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1686, 'Medicine', 'PM1219. Classification of Hypertension', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\144\>\n<p><strong>Types</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\293\>\n<p><strong>Features</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\144\>\n<p>Primary/ Essential/ Idiopathic Hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\293\>\n<p>Most common&nbsp;type</p>\n<p>Cause is unknown</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\144\>\n<p>Secondary hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\293\>\n<p>Usually correctable</p>\n<p>Has definitive cause</p>\n<p>Usually develops before 30yrs or after 55yrs</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\144\>\n<p>Isolated systolic hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\293\>\n<p><span class=\nowrap\>≥140/&lt;90</span> mmHg</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\144\>\n<p>Isolated diastolic hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\293\>\n<p><span class=\nowrap\>&lt;130/≥80 mmHg</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\144\>\n<p>Whitecoat hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\293\>\n<ul>\n<li>The office blood pressure is ≥140/90 mm Hg on ≥3 separate office visits</li>\n<li>≥2 blood pressure measurements taken outside the office are &lt;140/90 mm Hg, frequently using home blood pressure monitoring; and</li>\n<li>There is no evidence of hypertensive target organ damage.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1687, 'Medicine', 'PM1218. Classification of blood pressure for adults - European Society of Cardiology guidelines - 2018', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Classification of Office blood pressure</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>SBP (mmHg)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>DBP (mmHg)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Optimal&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>&lt;120 and</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>&lt;80</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Normal</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>120-129 and/or</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>80-84</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>High normal</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>130-139 and/or</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>85-89</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Grade 1 hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>140-159 and/or</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>90-99</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Grade 2 hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>160-179 and/or</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>100-109</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 3 hypertension</td>\n<td>≥180 and/or</td>\n<td>≥110</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Isolated systolic hypertension</td>\n<td>≥140 and</td>\n<td>&lt;90</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Note: Whenever hypertension can be classified into two different categories based on values of SBP and DBP, then the higher category is considered as the classification of hypertension.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1688, 'Medicine', 'PM1214. Classification of Congenital Heart Disease in Adults', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Simple</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Intermediate complexity</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Complex </strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Uncomplicated small ASD</li>\n<li>Uncomplicated Small VSD</li>\n<li>Mild pulmonic stenosis</li>\n<li>Occluded or ligated ductus arteriosus</li>\n<li>Repaired VSD without residue</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Ostium primum or sinus venous ASD</li>\n<li>AV canal defects</li>\n<li>Coarctation of Aorta</li>\n<li>Pulmonic valve stenosis</li>\n<li>PDA non closed</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Cyanotic congenital heart disease</li>\n<li>Ebstein anomaly</li>\n<li>Eisenmenger’s syndrome</li>\n<li>TOF</li>\n<li>Truncus arteriosus</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1689, 'Medicine', 'PM1212. Localisation of MI based on ST elevations in different leads', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Extensive anterior - I, aVL, V1-V6</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/a0d690cfd571427cabfe3625fec7aea2x720x446.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Lateral - I, aVL</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/544634fa03c146d38f02014738cc9ffdx1280x791.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Inferior - II, III, aVF</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/ecf1b037017145409598613d151004afx1280x808.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Anteroseptal - V1-V4</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/92955d71dfdd400ca4f634e482ddf9d8x1280x849.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Anterolateral - I, aVL, V3-V6</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/e2aaee158f5b4111b131cce1219c5afax1280x791.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Posterior - ST depression and tall R in V1-V4</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/dda0e5b11d9340808ac18534d35fd867x1280x803.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1690, 'Medicine', 'PM1208. Classification of Pulmonary Hypertension & its Causes', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Based on underlying mechanisms, the World Health Organization has classified pulmonary hypertension into five groups.</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Classification</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Causes</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Group 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Pulmonary arterial hypertension (PAH)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Idiopathic PAH</p>\n<p>Hereditary PAH - BMPR2 gene (most common mutation)</p>\n<p>Drug or toxin-induced PAH</p>\n<p>PAH associated with</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Connective tissue disorder (limited systemic sclerosis)</li>\n<li>Portal hypertension</li>\n<li>HIV</li>\n<li>Schistosomiasis</li>\n<li>Congenital heart diseases</li>\n</ul>\n<p>PAH long-term responders to calcium channel blockers</p>\n<p>PAH with overt features of a pulmonary veno-occlusive disease or pulmonary capillary hemangiomatosis</p>\n<p>Persistent pulmonary hypertension of the newborn syndrome</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Group 2</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Pulmonary hypertension associated with left heart disease </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Left ventricular systolic or diastolic dysfunction</p>\n<p>Valvular heart disease</p>\n<p>Congenital cardiomyopathies</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Group 3</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Pulmonary hypertension associated with lung</strong> <strong>disease</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease</p>\n<p>Interstitial lung disease</p>\n<p>Sleep-disordered breathing</p>\n<p>Alveolar hypoventilation disorders</p>\n<p>Chronic exposure to high altitude</p>\n<p>Developmental lung disorders</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Group 4</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Chronic thromboembolic pulmonary hypertension</p>\n<p>Congenital pulmonary artery stenosis</p>\n<p>Pulmonary arteritis</p>\n<p>Pulmonary angiosarcoma&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Group 5</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Pulmonary hypertension with unclear and/or multifactorial mechanisms</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Hematological disorders (chronic hemolytic anemias)</p>\n<p>Metabolic disorders (glycogen storage diseases)</p>\n<p>Systemic disorders (sarcoidosis)</p>\n<p>Others (tumor obstruction, fibrosing mediastinitis)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1691, 'Medicine', 'PM1205. Indication for Pacemaker in AV Conduction Defects', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<ul>\n<li>In any patient with symptomatic bradycardia</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<ul>\n<li>Irreversible second- or third-degree AV bloc</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<ul>\n<li>Pacing in patients with asymptomatic AV block should be individualized</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<p>With acquired CHB</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<p>Left ventricular dysfunction and</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<p>Waking heart rates 40 beats/min.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<ul>\n<li>Asymptomatic second-degree AV block of either type, if the block is demonstrated to be intra- or infra-His or is associated with a wide QRS complex</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\479\>\n<ul>\n<li>Neuromuscular diseases having a predilection for the conduction system, such as myotonic dystrophy and other muscular dystrophies, and Kearns-Sayre syndrome</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1692, 'Medicine', 'PM1204. Types of Heart block', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/321f89fee89642ff8d4791a7741dd90ax1280x1311.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1693, 'Medicine', 'PM1203. Etiology of Torsade De Pointes', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Acquired prolongation of QT interval</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Electrolyte abnormalities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Hypokalemia</li>\n<li>Hypomagnesemia</li>\n<li>Hypocalcemia</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Drugs</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Antiarrhythmic drugs</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Class IA: Quinidine, disopyramide, procainamide</li>\n<li>Class III: Sotalol, amiodarone (QT prolongation common but torsade ventricular tachycardia is rare), ibutilide, dofetilide, almokalant</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Antibiotics</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Macrolides: Erythromycin, clarithromycin, azithromycin</li>\n<li>Fluoroquinolones: Levofloxacin, moxifloxacin, gatifloxacin</li>\n<li>Trimethoprim-sulfamethoxazole</li>\n<li>Clindamycin</li>\n<li>Pentamidine</li>\n<li>Chloroquine</li>\n<li>Antifungals: Ketoconazole, itraconazole</li>\n<li>Antivirals</li>\n<li>Antipsychotics</li>\n<li>Antihistamines</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1694, 'Medicine', 'PM1202. Difference between VT and SVT with aberrancy', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>An ECG with a wide QRS complex can be seen in both VT and in SVT with aberrancy (the presence of a block or WPW syndrome). These two can be differentiated by the features given below:</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>Features </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>VT</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p><strong>SVT with aberrancy</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>QRS duration</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>&gt;0.14sec</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>0.12 – 0.14 sec</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>Fusion beats</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>+</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>-</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>Capture beats</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>+</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>unusual</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>AV dissociation</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>+</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>-</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>Independent P waves</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>+/-</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>-</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>QRS pattern</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>Does not resemble RBBB / LBBB</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>Resemble RBBB/ LBBB</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>Axis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>Left axis deviation</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>Normal or right</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>QRS morphology in V1</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>Monophasic or biphasic</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>Triphasic</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>R/S ratio in V6</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>&lt;1</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>&gt;1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\131\>\n<p><strong>Vagal manuvers</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p>No effect</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\154\>\n<p>Slowing / termination</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1695, 'Medicine', 'PM1201. Recommendations on use of Antithrombotics based on CHADS2 Score', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p><strong>CHADS2 score</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p><strong>Antithrombotics </strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>0</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p>Aspirin or no antithrombotics</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p>Aspirin or oral anticoagulant</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>&gt;1</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p>Oral anticoagulant</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1696, 'Medicine', 'PM1200. CHA2DS2-VASC scoring for risk of stroke  & need for oral anticoagulation in AF', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\441\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Components</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Points</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>C – Congestive heart failure</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>H - Hypertension</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>A – Age &gt; 75 years</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>D – Diabetes Mellitus</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>S – Stroke/TIA/TE</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>2</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p class=\p1\>VASc-Vascular disease (prior MI, Peripheral Arterial Disease,</p>\n<p class=\p1\>or aortic plaque)</p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;A- Age 65–74 years</td>\n<td>&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;S- sex category (i.e., female sex)</td>\n<td>&nbsp;1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p class=\p1\>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p><strong>CHADS2 score</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p><strong>Antithrombotics </strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>0</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p>Aspirin or no antithrombotics</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>1</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p>Aspirin or oral anticoagulant</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>&gt;1</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\280\>\n<p>Oral anticoagulant</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1697, 'Medicine', 'PM1199. Treatment algorithm in PSVT', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/3a21d597731d4ecdb43cd7e97f553095x563x438.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1698, 'Medicine', 'PM1198. Management of AR', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Stages of aortic regurgitation (AR):<br><br></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Stage</td>\n<td>Valve abnormalities</td>\n<td>Hemodynamic changes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>A</strong><br>(At risk of AR)</td>\n<td>\n<p>BAV<br><br>Valve sclerosis<br><br>Diseases of aortic sinus/ascending aorta<br><br>Rheumatic fever history/ RHD<br><br>IE</p>\n</td>\n<td>Not seen&nbsp;<br><br>Absent/trace aortic regurgitation</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>B</strong><br>(Pro-gressive AR)</td>\n<td>BAV<br><br>Valve calcification- mild/moderate<br><br>Dilated aortic sinuses<br><br>Rheumatic valve changes<br><br>IE</td>\n<td>LV systolic function- normal<br><br>LV dilatation- absent/mild</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>C</strong><br>(Asympto-matic severe AR)</td>\n<td>BAV<br><br>Calcific valve disease<br><br>Dilated aortic sinuses/ascending aorta<br><br>Rheumatic valve changes<br><br>IE with abnormal leaflet closure/perforation</td>\n<td><br><br>Stage C1-&nbsp;<br>LVEF- normal (&gt;55%)<br>LV dilatation- mild/moderate<br><br>Stage C2-<br>LVEF- decreased (≤55%)<br>LV dilatation- severe</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>D</strong><br>(Sympto-matic severe AR)</p>\n</td>\n<td>BAV<br><br>Calcific valve disease<br><br>Dilated aortic sinuses/ascending aorta<br><br>Rheumatic valve changes<br><br>IE with abnormal leaflet closure/perforation</td>\n<td>LVEF may be:<br>normal (&gt;55%)<br>Mild-moderate (40-55%)<br>severe (&lt;40%)<br><br>LV dilatation-moderate to severe</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p><br>BAV- Bicuspid aortic valve<br>IE- Infective endocarditis<br>RHD- Rheumatic heart disease<br>LV- Left ventricle<br>LVEF- Left ventricle ejection fraction<br><br></p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/65bfb35ee79f4a61af02c85b37ca6a5cx1280x2284.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1699, 'Medicine', 'PM1197. Mitral Regurgitation', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Stages of mitral regurgitation:<br><br></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Stage</td>\n<td>Valve prolapse and coaptation</td>\n<td>Hemodynamic changes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>A</strong><br>(At risk of MR)</td>\n<td>Prolapse- Mild<br>Coaptation- Normal</td>\n<td>Not seen&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>B</strong><br>(Progressive MR)</td>\n<td>Prolapse- Moderate to severe<br>Coaptation- Normal</td>\n<td>LA enlargement- mild<br>LV&nbsp;enlargement- absent<br>Pulmonary hypertension- not seen</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>C</strong><br>(Asymptomatic severe MR)</td>\n<td>Prolapse- Severe<br>Coaptation- Lost/ flail leaflets</td>\n<td>LA enlargement- moderate to severe<br>LV&nbsp;enlargement- present<br>Pulmonary hypertension- +/- at rest<br><br>Stage C1-&nbsp;<br>LVEF- &gt;60%<br>LVESD- &lt;40 mm<br><br>Stage C2-<br>LVEF- ≤60%<br>LVESD-&nbsp;≥ 40 mm</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p><strong>D</strong><br>(Symptomatic severe MR)</p>\n</td>\n<td>Prolapse- Severe<br>Coaptation- Lost/ flail leaflets</td>\n<td>LA enlargement- moderate to severe<br>LV&nbsp;enlargement- present<br>Pulmonary hypertension- present&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/f37fde7867ea48c4a5b5179596ca69fcx1280x2458.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1700, 'Medicine', 'PM1196. Management of MS', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/c13058822c034779954adb0e9ea5c6f7x892x531.PNG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li><strong>PCWP – Pulmonary capillary wedge pressure: PMBC – Percutaneous mitral balloon commissurotomy.</strong></li>\n<li><strong>MVR - Mitral valve surgery (repair/ replacement): T1/2 – Pressure halftime: MVA – Mitral valve area.</strong></li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1701, 'Medicine', 'PM1195. Different signs in Aortic Regurgitation', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p><strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>De Mussets sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>&nbsp;Head nodding with each heartbeat</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Collapsing/Water Hammer/Corrigan pulse</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p>&nbsp;It is a bounding pulse with rapid upstroke&nbsp; and descent</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Lighthouse sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>&nbsp;Alternate flushing &amp; blanching of the forehead</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Landolfi’s sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>&nbsp;Alternating constriction and dilation of the pupil</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Becker’s sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>&nbsp;Retinal artery pulsations</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Quincke’s pulse</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p>&nbsp;Alternate flushing and paling of the skin at the root of the nail while pressure is applied to the tip of the nail</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\><strong>Rosenbach’s sign</strong></td>\n<td width=\320\>&nbsp;Pulsation of liver</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\><strong>Gerhardt’s sign</strong></td>\n<td width=\320\>&nbsp;Pulsation over the spleen, detected in the presence of splenomegaly</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Traube’s sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p>&nbsp;A pistol shot sound over femoral arteries</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Durozeiz’s sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p>&nbsp;To-and-fro murmur over the femoral artery when lightly compressed with a stethoscope</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Hill’s sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p>&nbsp;The systolic blood pressure of the lower limb exceeds that of the upper limb at least by 20mm Hg</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\158\>\n<p><strong>Muller’s sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\320\>\n<p>Systolic pulsation of the uvula</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1702, 'Medicine', 'PM1194. Grading of Aortic Stenosis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\222\>\n<p><strong>Grading of stenosis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\221\>\n<p><strong>Area of aortic valve</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\222\>\n<p>Mild</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\221\>\n<p>1.5 – 2 sq cm</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\222\>\n<p>Moderate</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\221\>\n<p>1 – 1.5 sq cm</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\222\>\n<p>Severe</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\221\>\n<p>&lt; 1 sq cm</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1703, 'Medicine', 'PM1191. Causes of Valvular Heart Disease', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\176\>\n<p>Stenosis</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\302\>\n<p>Rheumatic fever</p>\n<p>Congenital</p>\n<p>Degenerative disease</p>\n<p>SLE</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\176\>\n<p>Regurgitation</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\302\>\n<p>Rheumatic fever</p>\n<p>Congenital</p>\n<p>Infective endocarditis</p>\n<p>Syphilitic Aortitis</p>\n<p>Trauma</p>\n<p>Myxomatous</p>\n<p>Marfan’s Syndrome</p>\n<p>HOCM</p>\n<p>Tumor</p>\n<p>Hypertension</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1704, 'Medicine', 'PM0653. Dynamic auscultation of murmurs', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Bedside Manoeuvre</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Effect</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Inspiration</p>\n<p>(↑venous return to right atrium)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>↑ intensity of right-sided sounds</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Handgrip</p>\n<p>(↑afterload )</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>↑ intensity of MR, AR, and VSD murmurs</li>\n<li>↓ hypertrophic cardiomyopathy and AS murmurs</li>\n<li>MVP: delayed onset of click/murmur</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Valsalva-Phase II, standing up</p>\n<p>(↓ preload)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>↓ intensity of most murmurs (including AS)</li>\n<li>↑&nbsp;intensity of hypertrophic cardiomyopathy murmur</li>\n<li>MVP: earlier onset of click /murmur</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Rapid squatting</p>\n<p>(↑venous return,↑preload,<br>↑ afterload)</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>↓intensity of hypertrophic cardiomyopathy murmur</li>\n<li>↑&nbsp;intensity of AS, MR, and VSD murmurs</li>\n<li>MVP: later onset of click/murmur</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1705, 'Medicine', 'PM0652. Risk Factors for Sudden Death in HCM', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Risk factors for sudden death in HCM:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>History of cardiac arrest or spontaneous sustained ventricular tachycardia</li>\n<li>Syncope</li>\n<li>Family history of sudden cardiac death</li>\n<li>Spontaneous nonsustained ventricular tachycardia</li>\n<li>LV thickness &gt; 30mm</li>\n<li>Abnormal blood pressure response to exercise</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1706, 'Medicine', 'PM0646. Definitions of Heart Failure According to EF (ESC HF guidelines 2016)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\374\>\n<p><strong>Newer definitions</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p><strong>Ejection fraction</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\374\>\n<p>Heart failure with reduced Ejection Fraction (HFrEF)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>≤40%</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\374\>\n<p><strong>Heart failure with preserved Ejection Fraction (HFpEF)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>≥50%</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\374\>\n<p>Heart failure with midrange Ejection Fraction (HFmrEF)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\163\>\n<p>40-49%</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1707, 'Medicine', 'PM0607. Signs in Pericardial Effusion', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\454\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p><strong>Sign</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\340\>\n<p><strong>Description</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p>Auenbrugger’s sign</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\340\>\n<p>Bulging of the epigastrium in severe pericardial effusion</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p>Moschcowitz’s sign</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\340\>\n<p>In pericardial effusion, the transition on percussion from the lungs to the right heart border is abrupt</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p>Dressler’s sign</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\340\>\n<p>Dullness to percussion of the lower half of the sternum, seen In pericardial effusion.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\114\>\n<p>Ewarts sign</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\340\>\n<p>In large pericardial effusion, compression of the base of the left lung by the pericardial fluid produces dullness and increased vocal fremitus beneath the angle of the left scapula.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1708, 'Medicine', 'PM0598. American Heart Association (AHA) recommendation for duration of secondary prophylaxis of rheumatic fever', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\454\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\227\>\n<p><strong>Category</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\227\>\n<p><strong>Duration after the last attack</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\227\>\n<p>Rheumatic fever without carditis</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\227\>&nbsp;\n<p>5 years or until 21 years of age (whichever is longer)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\227\>\n<p>Rheumatic fever with carditis but no residual heart disease (no valvular disease)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\227\>&nbsp;10 years or until 21 years of age (whichever is longer)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\227\>\n<p>Rheumatic fever with carditis and residual heart disease (persistent valvular disease)</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\227\>\n<p>10 years or until 40 years of age (whichever is longer), sometimes lifelong prophylaxis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1709, 'Medicine', 'PM0564. Causes of Pulsus Paradoxus', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>Physiological causes</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\262\>\n<p>Obesity</p>\n<p>Pregnancy</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>Cardiovascular causes</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\262\>\n<p>Cardiac tamponade – most common cause</p>\n<p>Constrictive pericarditis ( in 1/3<sup>rd</sup> cases )</p>\n<p>Massive pulmonary embolism</p>\n<p>Severe CCF</p>\n<p>Hypovolemic shock</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\177\>\n<p>Respiratory causes</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\262\>\n<p>Severe obstructive lung disease</p>\n<p>Acute severe asthma</p>\n<p>Severe emphysema</p>\n<p>Tension pneumothorax</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1710, 'Medicine', 'PM0555. Vascular diseases – Gender differences', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>More common in males</strong></td>\n<td><strong>More common in females</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p>Aortic aneurysm</p>\n<p>Aortic dissection</p>\n<p>Thromboangitis obliterans</p>\n<p>Erythromelalgia</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Fibromuscular</p>\n<p>Dysplasia</p>\n<p>Raynaud’s phenomenon</p>\n<p>Acrocyanosis</p>\n<p>Livedo reticularis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1711, 'Medicine', 'PM0544. Source of microorganisms causing infective endocarditis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table width=\419\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\210\>\n<p><strong>Microorganism </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\209\>\n<p><strong>Source </strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\210\>\n<p>Streptococcus viridans</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\209\>\n<p>Oral cavity</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\210\>\n<p>Staphylococcus aureus</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\209\>\n<p>Skin</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\210\>\n<p>HACEK organisms</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\209\>\n<p>Upper respiratory tract</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\210\>\n<p>Streptococcus gallolyticus</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\209\>\n<p>GIT (Colon )</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\210\>\n<p>Enterococci</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\209\>\n<p>Genitourinary tract</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1712, 'Medicine', 'PM2434. CSF findings in meningitis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Glucose&nbsp;</strong><br><strong>(mg/dL)</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Protein</strong><br><strong>(mg/dL)</strong></td>\n<td><strong>WBC (per&nbsp;μL)</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Normal</strong></td>\n<td>40-85</td>\n<td>15-45</td>\n<td>\n<p>&lt;5</p>\n<p>60-70% lymphocytes, ≤30% monocytes / macrophages</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Bacterial</strong></td>\n<td>&lt;40</td>\n<td>&gt;100</td>\n<td>\n<p>&gt;1000</p>\n<p>↑↑PMNs (≥80%)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Viral</strong></td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n<td>20-80</td>\n<td>\n<p>25-500</p>\n<p>Predominantly lymphocytes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Tuberculous</strong></td>\n<td>&lt;50 <br>in 75% cases</td>\n<td>100-200</td>\n<td>\n<p>25-100</p>\n<p>Predominantly lymphocytes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Fungal</strong></td>\n<td>↓ to normal</td>\n<td>150-300</td>\n<td>\n<p>40-600</p>\n<p>Lymphocytes or PMNs, depending on specific organism</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Parasitic</strong></td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n<td>50-200&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>150-2000</p>\n<p>↑↑ Eosinophils (≥50%)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1713, 'Medicine', 'PM2431. West haven criteria for grading of mental status', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 1</strong></td>\n<td>Trivial lack of awareness; euphoria or anxiety; shortened attention span; impaired performance of addition or subtraction.&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 2</strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;Lethargy or apathy; minimal disorientation for time or place; subtle personality change; inappropriate behaviour with easily detectable flapping tremors.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 3</strong></td>\n<td>&nbsp;Somnolence to semi stupor, but responsive to verbal stimuli; confusion; gross disorientation.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 4&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>Coma.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1714, 'Medicine', 'PM2083. Neurological Manifestations in Deficiency Diseases', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 1551\>\n<div class=\section\>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p><strong>Neurological</strong><br><strong> manifestations</strong></p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td><strong>Associated nutritional deficiencies</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dementia,&nbsp;encephalopathy</td>\n<td>Vitamin B12, nicotinic acid, thiamine, folate&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Seizures</td>\n<td>Pyridoxine</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Myelopathy</td>\n<td>Vitamin B12, vitamin E, folate, copper</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Myopathy</td>\n<td>Vitamin D, vitamin E</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Peripheral neuropathy</td>\n<td>Thiamine, vitamin B12, and many others</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Optic neuropathy</td>\n<td>Thiamine, vitamin B12, and many others</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1715, 'Medicine', 'PM2077. Neuropathic Disorders', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Hereditary neuropathic disorders&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Charcot-Marie-Tooth disease (Most common hereditary neuropathy)</li>\n<li>Tangier disease</li>\n<li>Friedreich’s ataxia</li>\n<li>Familial Amyloid Polyneuropathy</li>\n<li>Hereditary Neuropathy with Liability to Pressure Palsies (HNPP)</li>\n<li>Hereditary Neuralgic Amyotrophy (HNA)</li>\n<li>Hereditary Sensory and Autonomic Neuropathy (HSAN)</li>\n<li>Fabry’s disease (angiokeratoma corporis diffusum)</li>\n<li>Refsum’s disease</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Causes of&nbsp;acquired&nbsp;neuropathies</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Primary or AL amyloidosis</li>\n<li>Diabetic neuropathy</li>\n<li>Hypothyroidism</li>\n<li>Sjögren’s syndrome</li>\n<li>Rheumatoid arthritis (RA)</li>\n<li>Scleroderma, Sarcoidosis</li>\n<li>Infectious (VZV,CMV,EBV,Hepatitis, HIV, Diphtheria, Leprosy)&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Inflammatory bowel disease</li>\n<li>Critical illness polyneuropathy (CIP)</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 3595\>&nbsp;</div></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1716, 'Medicine', 'PM2076. Conditions causing sensorimotor neuropathy', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Conditions causing sensorimotor neuropathy&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Diabetes mellitus</li>\n<li>Uremia</li>\n<li>Porphyria</li>\n<li>Cryoglobulinemia</li>\n<li>Drugs (Amiodarone,&nbsp;Isoniazid, Metronidazole)</li>\n<li>Toxins (Arsenic<strong>,</strong>&nbsp;Diphtheria toxin, Organophosphates)</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->');
INSERT INTO db_pearl_m (pid, subject, pearl_title, pearl_desc) VALUES
(1717, 'Medicine', 'PM2075. Sensory Loss In peripheral Neuropathies', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Symmetrical Sensory Loss</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cryptogenic or idiopathic sensory polyneuropathy (CSPN)</li>\n<li>Diabetes mellitus and other metabolic disorders</li>\n<li>Drugs and toxins</li>\n<li>Familial (HSAN), CMT, amyloidosis</li>\n<li>Inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy (GBS and CIDP)&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Asymmetrical Sensory Loss</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cancer (paraneoplastic)</li>\n<li>Sjögren’s syndrome</li>\n<li>Idiopathic sensory neuronopathy (possible GBS variant)</li>\n<li>Cisplatin and other chemotherapeutic agents</li>\n<li>Vitamin B6 toxicity</li>\n<li>Multifocal CIDP, vasculitis, cryoglobulinemia, amyloidosis, sarcoid, infectious (leprosy, Lyme, hepatitis B, C, or E, HIV, CMV), tumor infiltration&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Compressive mononeuropathy, plexopathy, or radiculopathy</li>\n<li>Polyradiculopathy or plexopathy due to diabetes mellitus</li>\n<li>Cryptogenic or idiopathic sensory polyneuropathy (CSPN)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1718, 'Medicine', 'PM2073. Peripheral Neuropathies Without Sensory Loss', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>With Symmetrical Weakness</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Spinal muscular atrophy</li>\n<li>Hereditary motor neuropathy (“distal” spinal muscular atrophy) or atypical&nbsp;Charcot–Marie–Tooth disease (CMT)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>With Asymmetrical weakness &nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Motor neuron disease</li>\n<li>Progressive muscular atrophy</li>\n<li>Juvenile monomelic amyotrophy (Hirayama’s&nbsp; disease)</li>\n<li>\n<div>Multifocal motor neuropathy</div>\n</li>\n<li>\n<div>Multifocal acquired motor axonopathy</div>\n</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1719, 'Medicine', 'PM2072. Neuropathies associated with prominent autonomic dysfunction', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><div class=\page\ title=\Page 3593\>\n<ul>\n<li>Hereditary sensory and autonomic neuropathy</li>\n<li>Amyloidosis (familial and acquired)</li>\n<li>Diabetes mellitus</li>\n<li>Idiopathic pandysautonomia (may be a variant of Guillain-Barré syndrome)</li>\n<li>Porphyria</li>\n<li>HIV-related autonomic neuropathy</li>\n<li>Vincristine and other chemotherapeutic agents</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1720, 'Medicine', 'PM2051. Difference between various causes of ataxia', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Friedreichs&nbsp;</strong><strong>ataxia</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>&nbsp;Tabes&nbsp;</strong><strong>dorsalis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;SACD</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tract&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Posterior column</p>\n<p>Pyramidal&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Spinocerebellar tracts&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Posterior column</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Posterior column</p>\n<p>Pyramidal&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Peripheral nerves</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Vibration sense</td>\n<td>\n<p>Absent</p>\n</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n<td>Absent&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Proprioception</td>\n<td>\n<p>Absent</p>\n</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Pain/Temperature</td>\n<td>\n<p>Present</p>\n</td>\n<td>Present</td>\n<td>Present</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Deep tendon reflex</td>\n<td>\n<p>Absent</p>\n</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n<td>Present. Maybe lost later.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Babinski sign</td>\n<td>\n<p>Present</p>\n</td>\n<td>Not Present</td>\n<td>Present</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Features</td>\n<td>\n<p>Cardiomyopathy</p>\n<p>Optic atrophy</p>\n<p>Diabetes mellitus</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Argyll Robertson pupil</p>\n<p>Bladder disturbance</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Vitamin B12 deficiency</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>SACD-subacute combined degeneration</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1721, 'Medicine', 'PM2019. Parkinson plus syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Condition</strong></td>\n<td colspan=\2\><strong>Lesion</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>MSA/Shy dragger syndrome</td>\n<td rowspan=\5\>\n<p>Parkinson disease +</p>\n</td>\n<td>Dysautonomia&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>MSAc</td>\n<td>Cerebellar symptoms</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>MSAp</td>\n<td>Pyramidal symptoms&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Progressive supranuclear palsy</td>\n<td>Supranuclear palsy</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Lewy body dementia</td>\n<td>Early dementia&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>MSA - Multi System Atrophy</p>\n<p>Parkinson plus syndrome</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Faster progress of disease</li>\n<li>Poor response to levodopa</li>\n<li>Poor prognosis</li>\n<li>Increased mortality</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1722, 'Medicine', 'PM2018. Brain lesions and disease', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Area of lesion</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Description</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Disease</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Dominant parietal cortex</td>\n<td>Agraphia, acalculia, finger agnosia, left-right disorientation</td>\n<td>Gerstmann syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Non-dominant parietal cortex</td>\n<td>Agnosia of the contralateral side of the world</td>\n<td>Hemispatial neglect syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mammillary bodies<br>(bilateral)</td>\n<td>Confusion, Ataxia, Nystagmus, Ophthalmoplegia,<br>memory loss (anterograde and retrograde<br>amnesia), confabulation, personality changes.</td>\n<td>Wernicke-Korsakoff syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Amygdala (bilateral)</td>\n<td>hyperphagia, hypersexuality, hyperorality</td>\n<td>Klüver-Bucy syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Superior colliculus</td>\n<td>Paralysis of conjugate<br>vertical gaze (rostral interstitial nucleus also<br>involved)</td>\n<td>Parinaud syndrome</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1723, 'Medicine', 'PM2003. Trigeminal Autonomic Cephalalgia', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Types of trigeminal autonomic cephalalgia:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Cluster headache</li>\n<li>Paroxysmal hemicranias</li>\n<li>Short-lasting unilateral neuralgiform headache with conjunctival injection and tearing (SUNCT)</li>\n<li>Short-lasting unilateral neuralgiform&nbsp;<em>headache</em>&nbsp;attacks with cranial autonomic features (SUNA)</li>\n<li>Hemicrania continua</li>\n</ul>\n<table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;Cluster headache</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Paroxysmal hemicrania&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td><strong>&nbsp;SUNCT/SUNA</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Gender&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Males&gt;females</td>\n<td>Female=Males</td>\n<td>Female=Males</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Character of pain&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Stabbing /boring</td>\n<td>Throbbing pain&nbsp;/stabbing /boring</td>\n<td>Burning /stabbing/sharp</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Severity of pain&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Excruciating&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Excruciating</td>\n<td>Severe to excruciating</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Site of pain&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Orbit, temple</td>\n<td>Orbit, temple</td>\n<td>Periorbital</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Attack frequency&nbsp;</td>\n<td>1-8 /day</td>\n<td>1-20/day</td>\n<td>3-200/day</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Duration</td>\n<td>15min-3 hours</td>\n<td>2-30 min</td>\n<td>5-240seconds</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Migraneous feature&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Yes&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Yes&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Alcohol trigger&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Cutaneous trigger</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Response to indomethacin</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Abortive treatment</td>\n<td>\n<p>100% oxygen</p>\n<p>Sumatriptan injection</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>No effective treatment</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>IV lidocaine&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Prophylaxis</td>\n<td>\n<p>Chronic cluster</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Lithium</li>\n<li>Verapamil</li>\n<li>Methysergide</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Episodic cluster&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Steroids&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Verapamil</li>\n<li>Methysergide</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Indomethacin</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Lamotrigine</li>\n<li>Topiramate</li>\n<li>Gabapentin</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Indomethacin</strong> is effective in paroxysmal hemicrania,hemicrania continuum, and primary sexual/ exercise headache</li>\n<li>Cutaneous trigger is also seen in trigeminal neuralgia, however, <strong>trigeminal neuralgia</strong> is a <strong>separate entity </strong>and not a part of trigeminal autonomic cephalalgia&nbsp;</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1724, 'Medicine', 'PM1996. Simplified diagnostic criteria for migraine', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>Repeated attacks of headache lasting 4-72 h in patients with a normal physical examination with no other reasonable cause for the headache, and</p>\n<p><strong>At least 2 of the following features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Unilateral pain</li>\n<li>Throbbing pain</li>\n<li>Aggravation by movement</li>\n<li>Moderate or severe intensity</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Plus at least 1 of the following features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Nausea/vomiting</li>\n<li>Photophobia and phonophobia</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1725, 'Medicine', 'PM1989. Inflammatory myopathy', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td><strong>Dermatomyositis</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Polymyositis</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Inclusion Body Myositis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Age of onset</td>\n<td>Adulthood and childhood</td>\n<td>&gt;18 years</td>\n<td>&gt;50 years &nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Familial Association</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Skin Manifestation</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n<td>No</td>\n<td>No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Muscle involvement</td>\n<td>\n<p>Symmetric</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Symmetric</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Asymmetric</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Histopathological Findings</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Perimysial</strong>&nbsp;<strong>CD4+</strong>&nbsp;cellular infiltrates</p>\n<p>Perivascular infiltrates and <strong>perifascicular atrophy</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Endomysial</strong>&nbsp;<strong>CD8+</strong>&nbsp;cellular infiltrates&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Perivascular infiltrates&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p><strong>Endomysial</strong>&nbsp;<strong>CD8+</strong>&nbsp;cellular infiltrates</p>\n<p>Perivascular infiltrates with amyloid inclusion bodies and rimmed vacuoles &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Association with connective tissue disease</td>\n<td>Scleroderma and mixed connective tissue only</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n<td>Yes</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Association with other autoimmune diseases</td>\n<td>Infrequent</td>\n<td>Frequent</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Infrequent</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Association with malignancy</td>\n<td>Yes (most common- ovarian malignancy)</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Yes (incidence much lesser than dermatomyositis)</td>\n<td>&nbsp;No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Immunotherapy</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Responsive</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Responsive</td>\n<td>&nbsp;Resistant</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1726, 'Medicine', 'PM1980. Antibodies seen in Guillian Barre syndrome', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Type</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Antibody</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AIDP</td>\n<td>Anti GM1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AMAN</td>\n<td>Anti GD1a</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>AMSAN</td>\n<td>Anti GD1a</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Miller Fisher syndrome</td>\n<td>Anti GQ1b</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<ul>\n<li>AIDP-Acute inflammatory demyelinating polyneuropathy&nbsp;</li>\n<li>AMAN-Acute motor axonal neuropathy&nbsp;</li>\n<li>AMSAN-Acute motor sensory axonal neuropathy&nbsp;</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1727, 'Medicine', 'PM1930. Grading of hepatic encephalopathy - West Haven Criteria', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Clinical grade</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Clinical signs</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Category</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Minimal&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Abnormal psychometric or neurophysiological tests</p>\n<p>No clinical manifestations</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Covert HE</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 1</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Altered sleep pattern</p>\n<p>Changes in behavior</p>\n<p>Slurred speech</p>\n<p>Mild confusion</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Covert HE</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 2</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Disoriented</p>\n<p>Lethargic</p>\n<p>Inappropriate behavior</p>\n<p>Asterixis</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>&nbsp;Overt HE</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 3</strong></td>\n<td>\n<p>Stuporous</p>\n<p>Responds to pain and voice</p>\n<p>Gross disorientation</p>\n</td>\n<td>Overt HE</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade 4</strong>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>\n<p>Unresponsive to voice or pain</p>\n<p>Comatose</p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p>Overt HE</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1728, 'Medicine', 'PM1814. Stroke syndromes with visual symptoms', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p><strong>Disease</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p><strong>Site of lesion</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td width=\241\>\n<p><strong>Clinical features</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Anton’s syndrome</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>B/L infarction in the distal PCAs</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\241\>\n<p>Cortical blindness, with denial or unawareness of blindness</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Balint’s syndrome</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Low flow in the “watershed region” between distal PCA and MCA territories</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\241\>\n<p>Palinopsia</p>\n<p>Asimultanagnosia</p>\n<p>Optic ataxia</p>\n<p>Ocular apraxia</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Weber’s syndrome</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Midbrain</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\241\>\n<p>I/L CN III palsy</p>\n<p>C/L hemiplegia</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Parinaud’s syndrome</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Dorsal midbrain</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\241\>\n<p>Tetrad of symptoms:</p>\n<p>Loss of upgaze</p>\n<p>Light-near dissociation</p>\n<p>Convergence – retraction nystagmus</p>\n<p>Lid retraction</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\162\>\n<p>Benedikt syndrome</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\198\>\n<p>Midbrain</p>\n</td>\n<td width=\241\>\n<p>Ipsilateral oculomotor nerve palsy</p>\n<p>Contralateral hemiparesis</p>\n<p>Contralateral cerebellar ataxia</p>\n<p>Holmes tremor</p>\n<p>Choreoathetosis</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1729, 'Medicine', 'PM1813. ABCD2 Score', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p>The risk of stroke <strong>following TIAs</strong> is determined by <strong>ABCD<sup>2</sup> score:</strong></p>\n<table width=\475\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Risk factors</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Score</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>A</strong>ge&nbsp;<span>&gt;</span> 60&nbsp;</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>S<strong>B</strong>P&gt;140 mmHg or D<strong>B</strong>P &gt;90 mmHg</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\><strong>C</strong>linical symptoms:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Unilateral weakness</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Speech disturbances without&nbsp;weakness</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\2\><strong>D</strong>uration:</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>&gt;60 minutes</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>10 - 59 minutes</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>D</strong>iabetes</td>\n<td>1</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Total score</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Sum each score</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>ABCD2 Score Total</td>\n<td>3-months Rate of stroke (%)</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>0</td>\n<td>0</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2</td>\n<td>3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3</td>\n<td>3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4</td>\n<td>8</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5</td>\n<td>12</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6</td>\n<td>17</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7</td>\n<td>22</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1730, 'Medicine', 'PM1805. The Medical Research Council scale for grading the muscle strength is :', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Grade</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Description</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 0</td>\n<td>No contraction</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 1</td>\n<td>Flicker or trace of contraction</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 2</td>\n<td>Active movement with gravity eliminated</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 3</td>\n<td>Active movement against gravity</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 4&nbsp;</td>\n<td>Active movement against gravity and resistance</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Grade 5</td>\n<td>Normal Power</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1731, 'Medicine', 'PM1790. Mesial Temporal Lobe Epilepsy', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Mesial temporal lobe epilepsy</strong> shows a <strong>familial inheritance</strong> and begins in childhood. It presents as&nbsp;<strong>focal seizures&nbsp;</strong>with a remitting and relapsing course. It is associated with:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Aura</li>\n<li>Complex automatism</li>\n<li>Post-ictal confusion</li>\n<li>Anterograde amnesia</li>\n</ul>\n<p>EEG findings include <strong>temporal spikes</strong>, and MRI shows <strong>hippocampal sclerosis</strong>. Management includes <strong>anteromedial resection</strong> of the <strong>temporal lobe</strong>.</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <!---->\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\>\n        <img _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\img-responsive ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ src=\https://dhmbxeygs57ff.cloudfront.net/uploads/515b5573b7c34b1f9289e3b434b67a4ex1280x1669.JPEG\><!---->\n      </div><!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1732, 'Medicine', 'PM1788. Indications and Contraindications of thrombolysis in Ischemic Stroke', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Indications for thrombolysis in stroke</strong>&nbsp;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Clinical diagnosis of stroke</li>\n<li>Onset of symptoms to time of drug administration &lt;3 hours/<strong>4.5</strong> hours</li>\n<li>Age ≥ 18 years</li>\n<li>CT scan showing no haemorrhage or edema of &gt;1/3<sup>rd</sup> of the MCA territory&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Contraindications of thrombolysis in stroke&nbsp;</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Sustained BP &gt;185/110 mmHg despite treatment</li>\n<li>Bleeding diathesis</li>\n<li>Recent head injury or Intracerebral hemorrhage</li>\n<li>Major surgery in preceding 14 days</li>\n<li>Minor stroke symptoms</li>\n<li>Gastrointestinal bleeding in preceding 21 days</li>\n<li>Recent myocardial infarction</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1733, 'Medicine', 'PM1780. Revised criteria for the clinical diagnosis of probable and possible dementia with Lewy bodies (DLB)', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><ul>\n<li>Essential for a diagnosis of <strong>DLB </strong>is<strong> dementia</strong>, defined as a progressive cognitive decline of sufficient magnitude to interfere with normal social or occupational functions, or with usual daily activities.</li>\n<li>Prominent or persistent memory impairment may not necessarily occur in the early stages but is usually evident with progression.</li>\n<li>Deficits on tests of attention, executive function, and visuoperceptual ability may be especially prominent and occur early.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Core clinical features (The first 3 typically occur early and may persist throughout the course.)</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Fluctuating cognition</strong> with pronounced variations in attention and alertness.</li>\n<li><strong>Recurrent visual hallucinations</strong> that are typically well formed and detailed.</li>\n<li><strong>REM sleep behavior disorder</strong>, which may precede cognitive decline.</li>\n<li>One or more spontaneous <strong>cardinal features of Parkinsonism</strong>: these are bradykinesia (defined as slowness of movement and decrement in amplitude or speed), rest tremor, or rigidity.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Supportive clinical features:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Severe sensitivity to antipsychotic agents; postural instability; repeated falls; syncope or other transient episodes of unresponsiveness; severe autonomic dysfunction, e.g., constipation, <strong>orthostatic</strong> <strong>hypotension</strong>, urinary incontinence; hypersomnia; hyposmia; hallucinations in other modalities; systematized delusions; apathy, anxiety, and depression.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Indicative biomarkers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Reduced dopamine transporter uptake in basal ganglia demonstrated by SPECT or PET.</li>\n<li>Abnormal (low uptake) <sup>123</sup>iodine-MIBG myocardial scintigraphy.</li>\n<li>Polysomnographic confirmation of REM sleep without atonia.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Supportive biomarkers</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Relative preservation of medial temporal lobe structures on CT/MRI scan.</li>\n<li>Generalized low uptake on SPECT/PET perfusion/metabolism scan with reduced occipital activity ± the cingulate island sign on FDG-PET imaging.</li>\n<li>Prominent posterior slow-wave activity on EEG with periodic fluctuations in the pre-alpha/ theta range.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>A. Probable DLB can be diagnosed if:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Two or more core clinical features of DLB are present, with or without the presence of indicative biomarkers, or</li>\n<li>Only one core clinical feature is present, but with one or more indicative biomarkers</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Probable DLB should not be diagnosed on the basis of biomarkers alone</p>\n<p><strong>B. Possible DLB can be diagnosed if:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Only one core clinical feature of DLB is present, with no indicative biomarker evidence, or</li>\n<li>One or more indicative biomarkers is present but there are no core clinical features.</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1734, 'Medicine', 'PM1677. Intracranial Hypertension', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><p><strong>Definition</strong></p>\n<p>Intracranial hypertension is pressure within the cranium above normal. Normal range of ICP is 5-15mm Hg. Levels above 20-25mm Hg are usually treated.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Causes</strong>: Intracranial haemorrhage, brain tumors, head injury, meningitis, brain abscess, etc.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Symptoms of raised ICT</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Cushing’s triad</strong> – hypertension, bradycardia and respiratory depression</li>\n<li>Headache, visual blurring due to papilloedema and abducent nerve palsy&nbsp;</li>\n<li>Focal symptoms may arise due to the local effects in patients with mass lesions or due to herniation.</li>\n<li>Seizures</li>\n<li>Stroke</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Investigations</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>CT brain or MRI brain with gadolinium to rule out ICSOL&nbsp;</li>\n<li><strong>Lumbar puncture is contraindicated</strong> in the presence of raised ICT due to the risk of coning.</li>\n<li>Papilledema (as an indicator of ICT) should be ruled out before lumbar puncture.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Dexamethasone</li>\n<li>Ventriculotomy to remove CSF or ventriculoperitoneal shunt</li>\n<li>Decompressive craniectomy</li>\n<li>Surgical resection of ICSOL – by craniotomy or stereotactic radiosurgery</li>\n<li>Whole brain radiation for multiple metastases causing raised ICT</li>\n</ul></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1735, 'Medicine', 'PM1673. Signs that distinguish the origin of muscle weakness', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Sign</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Upper Motor Neuron</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Lower&nbsp;Motor Neuron</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Myopathic</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Psychogenic</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Atrophy</td>\n<td>None</td>\n<td>Severe</td>\n<td>Mild</td>\n<td>None</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Fasciculation</td>\n<td>None</td>\n<td>Common</td>\n<td>None</td>\n<td>None</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Tone</td>\n<td>Spastic</td>\n<td>Decreased</td>\n<td>Normal/ Decreased</td>\n<td>Variable/ paratonia</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Distribution of weakness</td>\n<td>Pyramidal/ regional</td>\n<td>\n<p>Distal/ segmental</p>\n</td>\n<td>Proximal</td>\n<td>Variable/ Inconsistent with daily activities</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Muscle stretch reflexs</td>\n<td>Hyperactive</td>\n<td>Hypoactive/ Absent</td>\n<td>Normal/ hypoactive</td>\n<td>Normal</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Babinski sign</td>\n<td>Present</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n<td>Absent</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1736, 'Medicine', 'PM1672. The 2017 Revised McDonald Diagnostic Criteria for Multiple Sclerosis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Clinical</strong><br><strong>(Attacks)</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Objective</strong><br><strong>Lesions</strong></td>\n<td><strong>Additional requirements to make the diagnosis</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 or more</td>\n<td>2 or more</td>\n<td>None*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 or more</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>None*</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2 or more</td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>Dissemination in space demonstrated by an additional clinical attack implicating a different CNS site or by MRI</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;1&nbsp;</td>\n<td>2 or more</td>\n<td>\n<p>Dissemination in time demonstrated by an additional clinical attack or by MRI</p>\n<p>or demonstration of CSF-specific oligoclonal bands</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;1<br><br></td>\n<td>1</td>\n<td>\n<p>Dissemination in space demonstrated by an additional clinical attack implicating a different CNS site or by MRI</p>\n<p><strong>AND</strong></p>\nDissemination in time demonstrated by an additional clinical attack or by MRI&nbsp;<strong>OR</strong> demonstration of CSF-specific oligoclonal bands</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>* No additional test needed. MRI considered in all cases. Spinal cord MRI or CSF examination in patients with insufficient clinical diagnosis</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<table border=\1\>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Definition of MRI evidence of</strong><br><strong>dissemination in space</strong></td>\n<td>T2 lesion in at least 2 of 4 MS-typical regions (peri-ventricular, juxtocortical, infratentorial,<br>or spinal cord)<br>Note: Gd-enhancing lesions are not required</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td><strong>Definition of MRI evidence of</strong><br><strong>dissemination in time</strong></td>\n<td>The simultaneous presence of Gd-enhancing and non-enhancing MRI lesions at any time<br>New T2 and/or Gd-enhancing lesion(s) on follow-up MRI</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Gd, gadolinium; MS, multiple sclerosis</p></div><!---->\n      <!---->\n    </div><!---->'),
(1737, 'Medicine', 'PM1671. Initial Symptoms In Multiple Sclerosis', '<div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\ style=\\>\n      <div _ngcontent-smq-c132=\\ class=\ng-tns-c132-18 ng-star-inserted\><div class=\page\ title=\Page 3580\>&nbsp;</div>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 3580\>\n<div class=\page\ title=\Page 3580\>\n<table><colgroup><col><col><col><col> </colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>&nbsp;Symptom</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Percentage of Cases</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Symptom</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Percentage of Cases</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Sensory loss</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>37</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Lhermitte</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>3</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Optic neuritis</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>36</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Pain</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>3</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Weakness</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>35</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>Dementia</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td>\n<div class=\layoutArea\>\n<div class=\column\>\n<p>2</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<div class=\la